53egl::ShareGroup *AllocateOrGetShareGroup(egl::Display *display, const gl::Context *shareContext)
54{
55 if (shareContext)
56 {
57 egl::ShareGroup *shareGroup = shareContext->getState().getShareGroup();
58 shareGroup->addRef();
59 return shareGroup;
60 }
61 else
62 {
63 return new egl::ShareGroup(display->getImplementation());
64 }
65}
66
67template <typename T>
68angle::Result GetQueryObjectParameter(const Context *context, Query *query, GLenum pname, T *params)
69{
70 ASSERT(query != nullptr || pname == GL_QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE_EXT);
71
72 switch (pname)
73 {
74 case GL_QUERY_RESULT_EXT:
75 return query->getResult(context, params);
76 case GL_QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE_EXT:
77 {
78 bool available = false;
79 if (context->isContextLost())
80 {
81 available = true;
82 }
83 else
84 {
85 ANGLE_TRY(query->isResultAvailable(context, &available));
86 }
87 *params = CastFromStateValue<T>(pname, static_cast<GLuint>(available));
88 return angle::Result::Continue;
89 }
90 default:
91 UNREACHABLE();
92 return angle::Result::Stop;
93 }
94}
95
96// Attribute map queries.
97EGLint GetClientMajorVersion(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
98{
99 return static_cast<EGLint>(attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_VERSION, 1));
100}
101
102EGLint GetClientMinorVersion(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
103{
104 return static_cast<EGLint>(attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_MINOR_VERSION, 0));
105}
106
107bool GetBackwardCompatibleContext(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
108{
109 return attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBLE_ANGLE, EGL_TRUE) == EGL_TRUE;
110}
111
112Version GetClientVersion(egl::Display *display, const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
113{
114 Version requestedVersion =
115 Version(GetClientMajorVersion(attribs), GetClientMinorVersion(attribs));
116 if (GetBackwardCompatibleContext(attribs))
117 {
118 if (requestedVersion.major == 1)
119 {
120 // If the user requests an ES1 context, we cannot return an ES 2+ context.
121 return Version(1, 1);
122 }
123 else
124 {
125 // Always up the version to at least the max conformant version this display supports.
126 // Only return a higher client version if requested.
127 return std::max(display->getImplementation()->getMaxConformantESVersion(),
128 requestedVersion);
129 }
130 }
131 else
132 {
133 return requestedVersion;
134 }
135}
136
137GLenum GetResetStrategy(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
138{
139 EGLAttrib attrib =
140 attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_RESET_NOTIFICATION_STRATEGY_EXT, EGL_NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION);
141 switch (attrib)
142 {
143 case EGL_NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION:
144 return GL_NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION_EXT;
145 case EGL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET:
146 return GL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET_EXT;
147 default:
148 UNREACHABLE();
149 return GL_NONE;
150 }
151}
152
153bool GetRobustAccess(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
154{
155 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_ROBUST_ACCESS_EXT, EGL_FALSE) == EGL_TRUE) ||
156 ((attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_FLAGS_KHR, 0) & EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_ROBUST_ACCESS_BIT_KHR) !=
157 0);
158}
159
160bool GetDebug(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
161{
162 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_DEBUG, EGL_FALSE) == EGL_TRUE) ||
163 ((attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_FLAGS_KHR, 0) & EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_DEBUG_BIT_KHR) != 0);
164}
165
166bool GetNoError(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
167{
168 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_NO_ERROR_KHR, EGL_FALSE) == EGL_TRUE);
169}
170
171bool GetWebGLContext(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
172{
173 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_WEBGL_COMPATIBILITY_ANGLE, EGL_FALSE) == EGL_TRUE);
174}
175
176bool GetExtensionsEnabled(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs, bool webGLContext)
177{
178 // If the context is WebGL, extensions are disabled by default
179 EGLAttrib defaultValue = webGLContext ? EGL_FALSE : EGL_TRUE;
180 return (attribs.get(EGL_EXTENSIONS_ENABLED_ANGLE, defaultValue) == EGL_TRUE);
181}
182
183bool GetBindGeneratesResource(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
184{
185 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_BIND_GENERATES_RESOURCE_CHROMIUM, EGL_TRUE) == EGL_TRUE);
186}
187
188bool GetClientArraysEnabled(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
189{
190 return (attribs.get(EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_ARRAYS_ENABLED_ANGLE, EGL_TRUE) == EGL_TRUE);
191}
192
193bool GetRobustResourceInit(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
194{
195 return (attribs.get(EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE, EGL_FALSE) == EGL_TRUE);
196}
197
198EGLenum GetContextPriority(const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
199{
200 return static_cast<EGLenum>(
201 attribs.getAsInt(EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LEVEL_IMG, EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_MEDIUM_IMG));
202}
203
204std::string GetObjectLabelFromPointer(GLsizei length, const GLchar *label)
205{
206 std::string labelName;
207 if (label != nullptr)
208 {
209 size_t labelLength = length < 0 ? strlen(label) : length;
210 labelName = std::string(label, labelLength);
211 }
212 return labelName;
213}
214
215void GetObjectLabelBase(const std::string &objectLabel,
216 GLsizei bufSize,
217 GLsizei *length,
218 GLchar *label)
219{
220 size_t writeLength = objectLabel.length();
221 if (label != nullptr && bufSize > 0)
222 {
223 writeLength = std::min(static_cast<size_t>(bufSize) - 1, objectLabel.length());
224 std::copy(objectLabel.begin(), objectLabel.begin() + writeLength, label);
225 label[writeLength] = '\0';
226 }
227
228 if (length != nullptr)
229 {
230 *length = static_cast<GLsizei>(writeLength);
231 }
232}
233
234// The rest default to false.
235constexpr angle::PackedEnumMap<PrimitiveMode, bool, angle::EnumSize<PrimitiveMode>() + 1>
236 kValidBasicDrawModes = {{
237 {PrimitiveMode::Points, true},
238 {PrimitiveMode::Lines, true},
239 {PrimitiveMode::LineLoop, true},
240 {PrimitiveMode::LineStrip, true},
241 {PrimitiveMode::Triangles, true},
242 {PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip, true},
243 {PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, true},
244 }};
245
246enum SubjectIndexes : angle::SubjectIndex
247{
248 kTexture0SubjectIndex = 0,
249 kTextureMaxSubjectIndex = kTexture0SubjectIndex + IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_ACTIVE_TEXTURES,
250 kImage0SubjectIndex = kTextureMaxSubjectIndex,
251 kImageMaxSubjectIndex = kImage0SubjectIndex + IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_IMAGE_UNITS,
252 kUniformBuffer0SubjectIndex = kImageMaxSubjectIndex,
253 kUniformBufferMaxSubjectIndex =
254 kUniformBuffer0SubjectIndex + IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDINGS,
255 kSampler0SubjectIndex = kUniformBufferMaxSubjectIndex,
256 kSamplerMaxSubjectIndex = kSampler0SubjectIndex + IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_ACTIVE_TEXTURES,
257 kVertexArraySubjectIndex = kSamplerMaxSubjectIndex,
258 kReadFramebufferSubjectIndex,
259 kDrawFramebufferSubjectIndex
260};
261
262bool IsClearBufferEnabled(const FramebufferState &fbState, GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer)
263{
264 return buffer != GL_COLOR || fbState.getEnabledDrawBuffers()[drawbuffer];
265}
266
267bool IsEmptyScissor(const State &glState)
268{
269 if (!glState.isScissorTestEnabled())
270 {
271 return false;
272 }
273
274 const Extents &dimensions = glState.getDrawFramebuffer()->getExtents();
275 Rectangle framebufferArea(0, 0, dimensions.width, dimensions.height);
276 return !ClipRectangle(framebufferArea, glState.getScissor(), nullptr);
277}
278
279bool IsColorMaskedOut(const BlendStateExt &blendStateExt, const GLint drawbuffer)
280{
281 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(drawbuffer) < blendStateExt.mMaxDrawBuffers);
282 return blendStateExt.getColorMaskIndexed(static_cast<size_t>(drawbuffer)) == 0;
283}
284} // anonymous namespace

286thread_local Context *gCurrentValidContext = nullptr;
287
288Context::Context(egl::Display *display,
289 const egl::Config *config,
290 const Context *shareContext,
291 TextureManager *shareTextures,
292 SemaphoreManager *shareSemaphores,
293 MemoryProgramCache *memoryProgramCache,
294 const EGLenum clientType,
295 const egl::AttributeMap &attribs,
296 const egl::DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions,
297 const egl::ClientExtensions &clientExtensions)
298 : mState(shareContext ? &shareContext->mState : nullptr,
299 AllocateOrGetShareGroup(display, shareContext),
300 shareTextures,
301 shareSemaphores,
302 &mOverlay,
303 clientType,
304 GetClientVersion(display, attribs),
305 GetDebug(attribs),
306 GetBindGeneratesResource(attribs),
307 GetClientArraysEnabled(attribs),
308 GetRobustResourceInit(attribs),
309 memoryProgramCache != nullptr,
310 GetContextPriority(attribs)),
311 mShared(shareContext != nullptr),
312 mSkipValidation(GetNoError(attribs)),
313 mDisplayTextureShareGroup(shareTextures != nullptr),
314 mDisplaySemaphoreShareGroup(shareSemaphores != nullptr),
315 mErrors(this),
316 mImplementation(display->getImplementation()
317 ->createContext(mState, &mErrors, config, shareContext, attribs)),
318 mLabel(nullptr),
319 mCompiler(),
320 mConfig(config),
321 mHasBeenCurrent(false),
322 mContextLost(false),
323 mResetStatus(GraphicsResetStatus::NoError),
324 mContextLostForced(false),
325 mResetStrategy(GetResetStrategy(attribs)),
326 mRobustAccess(GetRobustAccess(attribs)),
327 mSurfacelessSupported(displayExtensions.surfacelessContext),
328 mExplicitContextAvailable(clientExtensions.explicitContext),
329 mCurrentDrawSurface(static_cast<egl::Surface *>(EGL_NO_SURFACE)),
330 mCurrentReadSurface(static_cast<egl::Surface *>(EGL_NO_SURFACE)),
331 mDisplay(display),
332 mWebGLContext(GetWebGLContext(attribs)),
333 mBufferAccessValidationEnabled(false),
334 mExtensionsEnabled(GetExtensionsEnabled(attribs, mWebGLContext)),
335 mMemoryProgramCache(memoryProgramCache),
336 mVertexArrayObserverBinding(this, kVertexArraySubjectIndex),
337 mDrawFramebufferObserverBinding(this, kDrawFramebufferSubjectIndex),
338 mReadFramebufferObserverBinding(this, kReadFramebufferSubjectIndex),
339 mThreadPool(nullptr),
340 mFrameCapture(new angle::FrameCapture),
341 mRefCount(0),
342 mOverlay(mImplementation.get())
343{
344 for (angle::SubjectIndex uboIndex = kUniformBuffer0SubjectIndex;
345 uboIndex < kUniformBufferMaxSubjectIndex; ++uboIndex)
346 {
347 mUniformBufferObserverBindings.emplace_back(this, uboIndex);
348 }
349
350 for (angle::SubjectIndex samplerIndex = kSampler0SubjectIndex;
351 samplerIndex < kSamplerMaxSubjectIndex; ++samplerIndex)
352 {
353 mSamplerObserverBindings.emplace_back(this, samplerIndex);
354 }
355
356 for (angle::SubjectIndex imageIndex = kImage0SubjectIndex; imageIndex < kImageMaxSubjectIndex;
357 ++imageIndex)
358 {
359 mImageObserverBindings.emplace_back(this, imageIndex);
360 }
361
362 // Implementations now require the display to be set at context creation.
363 ASSERT(mDisplay);
364}
365
366void Context::initialize()
367{
368 mImplementation->setMemoryProgramCache(mMemoryProgramCache);
369
370 initCaps();
371
372 if (mDisplay->getFrontendFeatures().syncFramebufferBindingsOnTexImage.enabled)
373 {
374 mTexImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
375 mTexImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
376 }
377
378 mState.initialize(this);
379
380 mFenceNVHandleAllocator.setBaseHandle(0);
381
382 // [OpenGL ES 2.0.24] section 3.7 page 83:
383 // In the initial state, TEXTURE_2D and TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP have two-dimensional
384 // and cube map texture state vectors respectively associated with them.
385 // In order that access to these initial textures not be lost, they are treated as texture
386 // objects all of whose names are 0.
387
388 Texture *zeroTexture2D = new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::_2D);
389 mZeroTextures[TextureType::_2D].set(this, zeroTexture2D);
390
391 Texture *zeroTextureCube = new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::CubeMap);
392 mZeroTextures[TextureType::CubeMap].set(this, zeroTextureCube);
393
394 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 0) || mSupportedExtensions.texture3DOES)
395 {
396 Texture *zeroTexture3D = new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::_3D);
397 mZeroTextures[TextureType::_3D].set(this, zeroTexture3D);
398 }
399 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 0))
400 {
401 Texture *zeroTexture2DArray =
402 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::_2DArray);
403 mZeroTextures[TextureType::_2DArray].set(this, zeroTexture2DArray);
404 }
405 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 1) || mSupportedExtensions.textureMultisample)
406 {
407 Texture *zeroTexture2DMultisample =
408 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::_2DMultisample);
409 mZeroTextures[TextureType::_2DMultisample].set(this, zeroTexture2DMultisample);
410 }
411 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 1))
412 {
413 Texture *zeroTexture2DMultisampleArray =
414 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray);
415 mZeroTextures[TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray].set(this, zeroTexture2DMultisampleArray);
416
417 for (int i = 0; i < mState.mCaps.maxAtomicCounterBufferBindings; i++)
418 {
419 bindBufferRange(BufferBinding::AtomicCounter, i, {0}, 0, 0);
420 }
421
422 for (int i = 0; i < mState.mCaps.maxShaderStorageBufferBindings; i++)
423 {
424 bindBufferRange(BufferBinding::ShaderStorage, i, {0}, 0, 0);
425 }
426 }
427
428 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 2) || mSupportedExtensions.textureCubeMapArrayAny())
429 {
430 Texture *zeroTextureCubeMapArray =
431 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::CubeMapArray);
432 mZeroTextures[TextureType::CubeMapArray].set(this, zeroTextureCubeMapArray);
433 }
434
435 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 2) || mSupportedExtensions.textureBufferAny())
436 {
437 Texture *zeroTextureBuffer = new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::Buffer);
438 mZeroTextures[TextureType::Buffer].set(this, zeroTextureBuffer);
439 }
440
441 if (mSupportedExtensions.textureRectangle)
442 {
443 Texture *zeroTextureRectangle =
444 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::Rectangle);
445 mZeroTextures[TextureType::Rectangle].set(this, zeroTextureRectangle);
446 }
447
448 if (mSupportedExtensions.eglImageExternalOES ||
449 mSupportedExtensions.eglStreamConsumerExternalNV)
450 {
451 Texture *zeroTextureExternal =
452 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::External);
453 mZeroTextures[TextureType::External].set(this, zeroTextureExternal);
454 }
455
456 // This may change native TEXTURE_2D, TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES and TEXTURE_RECTANGLE,
457 // binding states. Ensure state manager is aware of this when binding
458 // this texture type.
459 if (mSupportedExtensions.webglVideoTexture)
460 {
461 Texture *zeroTextureVideoImage =
462 new Texture(mImplementation.get(), {0}, TextureType::VideoImage);
463 mZeroTextures[TextureType::VideoImage].set(this, zeroTextureVideoImage);
464 }
465
466 mState.initializeZeroTextures(this, mZeroTextures);
467
468 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->initialize());
469
470 bindVertexArray({0});
471
472 if (getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 0))
473 {
474 // [OpenGL ES 3.0.2] section 2.14.1 pg 85:
475 // In the initial state, a default transform feedback object is bound and treated as
476 // a transform feedback object with a name of zero. That object is bound any time
477 // BindTransformFeedback is called with id of zero
478 bindTransformFeedback(GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK, {0});
479 }
480
481 for (auto type : angle::AllEnums<BufferBinding>())
482 {
483 bindBuffer(type, {0});
484 }
485
486 bindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, {0});
487
488 for (int i = 0; i < mState.mCaps.maxUniformBufferBindings; i++)
489 {
490 bindBufferRange(BufferBinding::Uniform, i, {0}, 0, -1);
491 }
492
493 // Initialize GLES1 renderer if appropriate.
494 if (getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0))
495 {
496 mGLES1Renderer.reset(new GLES1Renderer());
497 }
498
499 // Initialize dirty bit masks
500 mAllDirtyBits.set();
501
502 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_ACTIVE_TEXTURES);
503 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER);
504 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_VERTEX_ARRAY);
505 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_TEXTURES);
506 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_PROGRAM);
507 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_SAMPLERS);
508 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_IMAGES);
509
510 mTexImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_UNPACK_STATE);
511 mTexImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_UNPACK_BUFFER_BINDING);
512 mTexImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_EXTENDED);
513 // No dirty objects.
514
515 // Readpixels uses the pack state and read FBO
516 mReadPixelsDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_PACK_STATE);
517 mReadPixelsDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_PACK_BUFFER_BINDING);
518 mReadPixelsDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
519 mReadPixelsDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER);
520
521 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_RASTERIZER_DISCARD_ENABLED);
522 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR_TEST_ENABLED);
523 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR);
524 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_VIEWPORT);
525 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_COLOR);
526 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_DEPTH);
527 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_STENCIL);
528 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_COLOR_MASK);
529 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_MASK);
530 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_WRITEMASK_FRONT);
531 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_WRITEMASK_BACK);
532 mClearDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
533 mClearDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER);
534
535 // We sync the draw Framebuffer manually in prepareForClear to allow the clear calls to do
536 // more custom handling for robust resource init.
537
538 mBlitDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR_TEST_ENABLED);
539 mBlitDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR);
540 mBlitDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_FRAMEBUFFER_SRGB);
541 mBlitDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
542 mBlitDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
543 mBlitDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER);
544 mBlitDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER);
545
546 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDING);
547 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDINGS);
548 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_BINDING);
549 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_PROGRAM_BINDING);
550 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE);
551 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_TEXTURE_BINDINGS);
552 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLER_BINDINGS);
553 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_IMAGE_BINDINGS);
554 mComputeDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_DISPATCH_INDIRECT_BUFFER_BINDING);
555 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_ACTIVE_TEXTURES);
556 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_TEXTURES);
557 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_PROGRAM);
558 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_IMAGES);
559 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_SAMPLERS);
560
561 mCopyImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
562 mCopyImageDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER);
563
564 // Initialize overlay after implementation is initialized.
565 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mOverlay.init(this));
566}
567
568egl::Error Context::onDestroy(const egl::Display *display)
569{
570 // Dump frame capture if enabled.
571 mFrameCapture->onDestroyContext(this);
572
573 if (mGLES1Renderer)
574 {
575 mGLES1Renderer->onDestroy(this, &mState);
576 }
577
578 ANGLE_TRY(unMakeCurrent(display));
579
580 for (auto fence : mFenceNVMap)
581 {
582 if (fence.second)
583 {
584 fence.second->onDestroy(this);
585 }
586 SafeDelete(fence.second);
587 }
588 mFenceNVMap.clear();
589
590 for (auto query : mQueryMap)
591 {
592 if (query.second != nullptr)
593 {
594 query.second->release(this);
595 }
596 }
597 mQueryMap.clear();
598
599 for (auto vertexArray : mVertexArrayMap)
600 {
601 if (vertexArray.second)
602 {
603 vertexArray.second->onDestroy(this);
604 }
605 }
606 mVertexArrayMap.clear();
607
608 for (auto transformFeedback : mTransformFeedbackMap)
609 {
610 if (transformFeedback.second != nullptr)
611 {
612 transformFeedback.second->release(this);
613 }
614 }
615 mTransformFeedbackMap.clear();
616
617 for (BindingPointer<Texture> &zeroTexture : mZeroTextures)
618 {
619 if (zeroTexture.get() != nullptr)
620 {
621 zeroTexture.set(this, nullptr);
622 }
623 }
624
625 releaseShaderCompiler();
626
627 mState.reset(this);
628
629 mState.mBufferManager->release(this);
630 // mProgramPipelineManager must be before mShaderProgramManager to give each
631 // PPO the chance to release any references they have to the Programs that
632 // are bound to them before the Programs are released()'ed.
633 mState.mProgramPipelineManager->release(this);
634 mState.mShaderProgramManager->release(this);
635 mState.mTextureManager->release(this);
636 mState.mRenderbufferManager->release(this);
637 mState.mSamplerManager->release(this);
638 mState.mSyncManager->release(this);
639 mState.mFramebufferManager->release(this);
640 mState.mMemoryObjectManager->release(this);
641 mState.mSemaphoreManager->release(this);
642
643 mThreadPool.reset();
644
645 mImplementation->onDestroy(this);
646
647 // Backend requires implementation to be destroyed first to close down all the objects
648 mState.mShareGroup->release(display);
649
650 mOverlay.destroy(this);
651
652 return egl::NoError();
653}
654
655Context::~Context() {}
656
657void Context::setLabel(EGLLabelKHR label)
658{
659 mLabel = label;
660}
661
662EGLLabelKHR Context::getLabel() const
663{
664 return mLabel;
665}
666
667egl::Error Context::makeCurrent(egl::Display *display,
668 egl::Surface *drawSurface,
669 egl::Surface *readSurface)
670{
671 mDisplay = display;
672
673 if (!mHasBeenCurrent)
674 {
675 initialize();
676 initRendererString();
677 initVersionStrings();
678 initExtensionStrings();
679
680 int width = 0;
681 int height = 0;
682 if (drawSurface != nullptr)
683 {
684 width = drawSurface->getWidth();
685 height = drawSurface->getHeight();
686 }
687
688 mState.setViewportParams(0, 0, width, height);
689 mState.setScissorParams(0, 0, width, height);
690
691 mHasBeenCurrent = true;
692 }
693
694 mFrameCapture->onMakeCurrent(this, drawSurface);
695
696 // TODO(jmadill): Rework this when we support ContextImpl
697 mState.setAllDirtyBits();
698 mState.setAllDirtyObjects();
699
700 ANGLE_TRY(setDefaultFramebuffer(drawSurface, readSurface));
701
702 // Notify the renderer of a context switch.
703 angle::Result implResult = mImplementation->onMakeCurrent(this);
704
705 // If the implementation fails onMakeCurrent, unset the default framebuffer.
706 if (implResult != angle::Result::Continue)
707 {
708 ANGLE_TRY(unsetDefaultFramebuffer());
709 return angle::ResultToEGL(implResult);
710 }
711
712 return egl::NoError();
713}
714
715egl::Error Context::unMakeCurrent(const egl::Display *display)
716{
717 ANGLE_TRY(angle::ResultToEGL(mImplementation->onUnMakeCurrent(this)));
718
719 ANGLE_TRY(unsetDefaultFramebuffer());
720
721 // Return the scratch buffers to the display so they can be shared with other contexts while
722 // this one is not current.
723 if (mScratchBuffer.valid())
724 {
725 mDisplay->returnScratchBuffer(mScratchBuffer.release());
726 }
727 if (mZeroFilledBuffer.valid())
728 {
729 mDisplay->returnZeroFilledBuffer(mZeroFilledBuffer.release());
730 }
731
732 return egl::NoError();
733}

768void Context::genFencesNV(GLsizei n, FenceNVID *fences)
769{
770 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
771 {
772 GLuint handle = mFenceNVHandleAllocator.allocate();
773 mFenceNVMap.assign({handle}, new FenceNV(mImplementation.get()));
774 fences[i] = {handle};
775 }
776}

779{

781}
782
783GLuint Context::createShaderProgramv(ShaderType type, GLsizei count, const GLchar *const *strings)
784{
785 const ShaderProgramID shaderID = FromGL<ShaderProgramID>(createShader(type));
786 if (shaderID.value)
787 {
788 Shader *shaderObject = getShader(shaderID);
789 ASSERT(shaderObject);
790 shaderObject->setSource(count, strings, nullptr);
791 shaderObject->compile(this);
792 const ShaderProgramID programID = FromGL<ShaderProgramID>(createProgram());
793 if (programID.value)
794 {
795 gl::Program *programObject = getProgramNoResolveLink(programID);
796 ASSERT(programObject);
797
798 if (shaderObject->isCompiled())
799 {
800 // As per Khronos issue 2261:
801 // https://gitlab.khronos.org/Tracker/vk-gl-cts/issues/2261
802 // We must wait to mark the program separable until it's successfully compiled.
803 programObject->setSeparable(true);
804
805 programObject->attachShader(this, shaderObject);
806
807 if (programObject->link(this) != angle::Result::Continue)
808 {
809 deleteShader(shaderID);
810 deleteProgram(programID);
811 return 0u;
812 }
813 if (onProgramLink(programObject) != angle::Result::Continue)
814 {
815 deleteShader(shaderID);
816 deleteProgram(programID);
817 return 0u;
818 }
819
820 // Need to manually resolveLink(), since onProgramLink() doesn't think the program
821 // is in use. For the normal glDetachShader() API call path, this is done during
822 // ValidateDetachShader() via gl::GetValidProgram().
823 programObject->resolveLink(this);
824 programObject->detachShader(this, shaderObject);
825 }
826
827 InfoLog &programInfoLog = programObject->getExecutable().getInfoLog();
828 programInfoLog << shaderObject->getInfoLogString();
829 }
830
831 deleteShader(shaderID);
832
833 return programID.value;
834 }
835
836 return 0u;
837}

889
890void Context::deleteSync(GLsync sync)
891{
892 // The spec specifies the underlying Fence object is not deleted until all current
893 // wait commands finish. However, since the name becomes invalid, we cannot query the fence,
894 // and since our API is currently designed for being called from a single thread, we can delete
895 // the fence immediately.
896 mState.mSyncManager->deleteObject(this, static_cast<GLuint>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(sync)));
897}

902 if (pipeline)
903 {

905 }
906
907 mState.mProgramPipelineManager->deleteObject(this, pipelineID);
908}

937
938void Context::deleteFencesNV(GLsizei n, const FenceNVID *fences)
939{
940 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
941 {
942 FenceNVID fence = fences[i];
943
944 FenceNV *fenceObject = nullptr;
945 if (mFenceNVMap.erase(fence, &fenceObject))
946 {
947 mFenceNVHandleAllocator.release(fence.value);
948 if (fenceObject)
949 {
950 fenceObject->onDestroy(this);
951 }
952 delete fenceObject;
953 }
954 }
955}

997gl::LabeledObject *Context::getLabeledObject(GLenum identifier, GLuint name) const
998{
999 switch (identifier)
1000 {
1001 case GL_BUFFER:
1002 return getBuffer({name});
1003 case GL_SHADER:
1004 return getShader({name});
1005 case GL_PROGRAM:
1006 return getProgramNoResolveLink({name});
1007 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY:
1008 return getVertexArray({name});
1009 case GL_QUERY:
1010 return getQuery({name});
1011 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK:
1012 return getTransformFeedback({name});
1013 case GL_SAMPLER:
1014 return getSampler({name});
1015 case GL_TEXTURE:
1016 return getTexture({name});
1017 case GL_RENDERBUFFER:
1018 return getRenderbuffer({name});
1019 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER:
1020 return getFramebuffer({name});
1021 case GL_PROGRAM_PIPELINE:
1022 return getProgramPipeline({name});
1023 default:
1024 UNREACHABLE();
1025 return nullptr;
1026 }
1027}

1029gl::LabeledObject *Context::getLabeledObjectFromPtr(const void *ptr) const
1030{
1031 return getSync(reinterpret_cast<GLsync>(const_cast<void *>(ptr)));
1032}

1035{

1037 ASSERT(object != nullptr);
1038

1040 object->setLabel(this, labelName);
1041
1042 // TODO(jmadill): Determine if the object is dirty based on 'name'. Conservatively assume the
1043 // specified object is active until we do this.
1044 mState.setObjectDirty(identifier);
1045}

1083void Context::bindTexture(TextureType target, TextureID handle)
1084{
1085 Texture *texture = nullptr;
1086
1087 if (handle.value == 0)
1088 {
1089 texture = mZeroTextures[target].get();
1090 }
1091 else
1092 {
1093 texture =
1094 mState.mTextureManager->checkTextureAllocation(mImplementation.get(), handle, target);
1095 }
1096
1097 ASSERT(texture);
1098 mState.setSamplerTexture(this, target, texture);
1099 mStateCache.onActiveTextureChange(this);
1100}

1108}

1196
1197void Context::beginQuery(QueryType target, QueryID query)
1198{
1199 Query *queryObject = getOrCreateQuery(query, target);
1200 ASSERT(queryObject);
1201
1202 // begin query
1203 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(queryObject->begin(this));
1204
1205 // set query as active for specified target only if begin succeeded
1206 mState.setActiveQuery(this, target, queryObject);
1207 mStateCache.onQueryChange(this);
1208}
1209
1210void Context::endQuery(QueryType target)
1211{
1212 Query *queryObject = mState.getActiveQuery(target);
1213 ASSERT(queryObject);
1214
1215 // Intentionally don't call try here. We don't want an early return.
1216 (void)(queryObject->end(this));
1217
1218 // Always unbind the query, even if there was an error. This may delete the query object.
1219 mState.setActiveQuery(this, target, nullptr);
1220 mStateCache.onQueryChange(this);
1221}
1222
1223void Context::queryCounter(QueryID id, QueryType target)
1224{
1225 ASSERT(target == QueryType::Timestamp);
1226
1227 Query *queryObject = getOrCreateQuery(id, target);
1228 ASSERT(queryObject);
1229
1230 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(queryObject->queryCounter(this));
1231}
1232
1233void Context::getQueryiv(QueryType target, GLenum pname, GLint *params)
1234{
1235 switch (pname)
1236 {
1237 case GL_CURRENT_QUERY_EXT:
1238 params[0] = mState.getActiveQueryId(target).value;
1239 break;
1240 case GL_QUERY_COUNTER_BITS_EXT:
1241 switch (target)
1242 {
1243 case QueryType::TimeElapsed:
1244 params[0] = getExtensions().queryCounterBitsTimeElapsed;
1245 break;
1246 case QueryType::Timestamp:
1247 params[0] = getExtensions().queryCounterBitsTimestamp;
1248 break;
1249 default:
1250 UNREACHABLE();
1251 params[0] = 0;
1252 break;
1253 }
1254 break;
1255 default:
1256 UNREACHABLE();
1257 return;
1258 }
1259}

1345
1346Query *Context::getOrCreateQuery(QueryID handle, QueryType type)
1347{
1348 if (!mQueryMap.contains(handle))
1349 {
1350 return nullptr;
1351 }
1352
1353 Query *query = mQueryMap.query(handle);
1354 if (!query)
1355 {
1356 ASSERT(type != QueryType::InvalidEnum);
1357 query = new Query(mImplementation.get(), type, handle);
1358 query->addRef();
1359 mQueryMap.assign(handle, query);
1360 }
1361 return query;
1362}
1363
1364Query *Context::getQuery(QueryID handle) const
1365{
1366 return mQueryMap.query(handle);
1367}

1393
1394void Context::getBooleanvImpl(GLenum pname, GLboolean *params) const
1395{
1396 switch (pname)
1397 {
1398 case GL_SHADER_COMPILER:
1399 *params = GL_TRUE;
1400 break;
1401 case GL_CONTEXT_ROBUST_ACCESS_EXT:
1402 *params = ConvertToGLBoolean(mRobustAccess);
1403 break;
1404
1405 default:
1406 mState.getBooleanv(pname, params);
1407 break;
1408 }
1409}
1410
1411void Context::getFloatvImpl(GLenum pname, GLfloat *params) const
1412{
1413 // Queries about context capabilities and maximums are answered by Context.
1414 // Queries about current GL state values are answered by State.
1415 switch (pname)
1416 {
1417 case GL_ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE:
1418 params[0] = mState.mCaps.minAliasedLineWidth;
1419 params[1] = mState.mCaps.maxAliasedLineWidth;
1420 break;
1421 case GL_ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE:
1422 params[0] = mState.mCaps.minAliasedPointSize;
1423 params[1] = mState.mCaps.maxAliasedPointSize;
1424 break;
1425 case GL_SMOOTH_POINT_SIZE_RANGE:
1426 params[0] = mState.mCaps.minSmoothPointSize;
1427 params[1] = mState.mCaps.maxSmoothPointSize;
1428 break;
1429 case GL_SMOOTH_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE:
1430 params[0] = mState.mCaps.minSmoothLineWidth;
1431 params[1] = mState.mCaps.maxSmoothLineWidth;
1432 break;
1433 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
1434 ASSERT(mState.mExtensions.textureFilterAnisotropic);
1435 *params = mState.mExtensions.maxTextureAnisotropy;
1436 break;
1437 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_LOD_BIAS:
1438 *params = mState.mCaps.maxLODBias;
1439 break;
1440 case GL_MIN_FRAGMENT_INTERPOLATION_OFFSET:
1441 *params = mState.mCaps.minInterpolationOffset;
1442 break;
1443 case GL_MAX_FRAGMENT_INTERPOLATION_OFFSET:
1444 *params = mState.mCaps.maxInterpolationOffset;
1445 break;
1446 default:
1447 mState.getFloatv(pname, params);
1448 break;
1449 }
1450}
1451
1452void Context::getIntegervImpl(GLenum pname, GLint *params) const
1453{
1454 // Queries about context capabilities and maximums are answered by Context.
1455 // Queries about current GL state values are answered by State.
1456
1457 switch (pname)
1458 {
1459 case GL_MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS:
1460 *params = mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttributes;
1461 break;
1462 case GL_MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS:
1463 *params = mState.mCaps.maxVertexUniformVectors;
1464 break;
1465 case GL_MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS:
1466 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformComponents[ShaderType::Vertex];
1467 break;
1468 case GL_MAX_VARYING_VECTORS:
1469 *params = mState.mCaps.maxVaryingVectors;
1470 break;
1471 case GL_MAX_VARYING_COMPONENTS:
1472 *params = mState.mCaps.maxVaryingVectors * 4;
1473 break;
1474 case GL_MAX_COMBINED_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS:
1475 *params = mState.mCaps.maxCombinedTextureImageUnits;
1476 break;
1477 case GL_MAX_VERTEX_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS:
1478 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderTextureImageUnits[ShaderType::Vertex];
1479 break;
1480 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS:
1481 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderTextureImageUnits[ShaderType::Fragment];
1482 break;
1483 case GL_MAX_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_VECTORS:
1484 *params = mState.mCaps.maxFragmentUniformVectors;
1485 break;
1486 case GL_MAX_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS:
1487 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformComponents[ShaderType::Fragment];
1488 break;

1491 break;
1492 case GL_MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS_EXT:

1524 break;

1527 break;

1560 break;

1563 break;
1564 case GL_NUM_COMPRESSED_TEXTURE_FORMATS:

1566 break;

1801 break;

1803 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderAtomicCounters[ShaderType::Geometry];
1804 break;

1806 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderImageUniforms[ShaderType::Geometry];
1807 break;

1809 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderStorageBlocks[ShaderType::Geometry];
1810 break;

1812 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_UNITS:
1813 *params = mState.mCaps.maxMultitextureUnits;
1814 break;

1820 break;

1822 *params = mState.mCaps.maxTextureMatrixStackDepth;
1823 break;
1824 case GL_MAX_LIGHTS:
1825 *params = mState.mCaps.maxLights;
1826 break;
1827
1828 // case GL_MAX_CLIP_DISTANCES_EXT: Conflict enum value
1829 case GL_MAX_CLIP_PLANES:
1830 if (getClientVersion().major >= 2)
1831 {
1832 // GL_APPLE_clip_distance/GL_EXT_clip_cull_distance
1833 *params = mState.mCaps.maxClipDistances;
1834 }
1835 else
1836 {
1837 *params = mState.mCaps.maxClipPlanes;
1838 }
1839 break;
1840 // GLES1 emulation: Vertex attribute queries
1841 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
1842 case GL_NORMAL_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
1843 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
1844 case GL_POINT_SIZE_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING_OES:
1845 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
1846 getIntegerVertexAttribImpl(pname, GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING, params);
1847 break;
1848 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_STRIDE:
1849 case GL_NORMAL_ARRAY_STRIDE:
1850 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY_STRIDE:
1851 case GL_POINT_SIZE_ARRAY_STRIDE_OES:
1852 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY_STRIDE:
1853 getIntegerVertexAttribImpl(pname, GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_STRIDE, params);
1854 break;
1855 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_SIZE:
1856 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY_SIZE:
1857 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY_SIZE:
1858 getIntegerVertexAttribImpl(pname, GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_SIZE, params);
1859 break;
1860 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_TYPE:
1861 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
1862 case GL_NORMAL_ARRAY_TYPE:
1863 case GL_POINT_SIZE_ARRAY_TYPE_OES:
1864 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY_TYPE:
1865 getIntegerVertexAttribImpl(pname, GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_TYPE, params);
1866 break;
1867
1868 // GL_KHR_parallel_shader_compile
1869 case GL_MAX_SHADER_COMPILER_THREADS_KHR:
1870 *params = mState.getMaxShaderCompilerThreads();
1871 break;
1872
1873 // GL_EXT_blend_func_extended
1874 case GL_MAX_DUAL_SOURCE_DRAW_BUFFERS_EXT:
1875 *params = mState.mExtensions.maxDualSourceDrawBuffers;
1876 break;
1877
1878 // OES_shader_multisample_interpolation
1879 case GL_FRAGMENT_INTERPOLATION_OFFSET_BITS_OES:
1880 *params = mState.mCaps.subPixelInterpolationOffsetBits;
1881 break;
1882
1883 // GL_OES_texture_buffer
1884 case GL_MAX_TEXTURE_BUFFER_SIZE:
1885 *params = mState.mCaps.maxTextureBufferSize;
1886 break;
1887 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_OFFSET_ALIGNMENT:
1888 *params = mState.mCaps.textureBufferOffsetAlignment;
1889 break;
1890
1891 default:
1892 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.getIntegerv(this, pname, params));
1893 break;
1894 }
1895}

1897void Context::getIntegerVertexAttribImpl(GLenum pname, GLenum attribpname, GLint *params) const
1898{
1899 getVertexAttribivImpl(static_cast<GLuint>(vertexArrayIndex(ParamToVertexArrayType(pname))),
1900 attribpname, params);
1901}
1902
1903void Context::getInteger64vImpl(GLenum pname, GLint64 *params) const
1904{
1905 // Queries about context capabilities and maximums are answered by Context.
1906 // Queries about current GL state values are answered by State.
1907 switch (pname)
1908 {
1909 case GL_MAX_ELEMENT_INDEX:
1910 *params = mState.mCaps.maxElementIndex;
1911 break;
1912 case GL_MAX_UNIFORM_BLOCK_SIZE:
1913 *params = mState.mCaps.maxUniformBlockSize;
1914 break;
1915 case GL_MAX_COMBINED_VERTEX_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS:
1916 *params = mState.mCaps.maxCombinedShaderUniformComponents[ShaderType::Vertex];
1917 break;
1918 case GL_MAX_COMBINED_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS:
1919 *params = mState.mCaps.maxCombinedShaderUniformComponents[ShaderType::Fragment];
1920 break;
1921 case GL_MAX_SERVER_WAIT_TIMEOUT:
1922 *params = mState.mCaps.maxServerWaitTimeout;
1923 break;
1924
1925 // GL_EXT_disjoint_timer_query
1926 case GL_TIMESTAMP_EXT:
1927 *params = mImplementation->getTimestamp();
1928 break;
1929
1930 case GL_MAX_SHADER_STORAGE_BLOCK_SIZE:
1931 *params = mState.mCaps.maxShaderStorageBlockSize;
1932 break;
1933 default:
1934 UNREACHABLE();
1935 break;
1936 }
1937}

1951
1952void Context::getIntegeri_v(GLenum target, GLuint index, GLint *data)
1953{
1954 // Queries about context capabilities and maximums are answered by Context.
1955 // Queries about current GL state values are answered by State.
1956
1957 GLenum nativeType;
1958 unsigned int numParams;
1959 bool queryStatus = getIndexedQueryParameterInfo(target, &nativeType, &numParams);
1960 ASSERT(queryStatus);
1961
1962 if (nativeType == GL_INT)
1963 {
1964 switch (target)
1965 {
1966 case GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_COUNT:
1967 ASSERT(index < 3u);
1968 *data = mState.mCaps.maxComputeWorkGroupCount[index];
1969 break;
1970 case GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE:
1971 ASSERT(index < 3u);
1972 *data = mState.mCaps.maxComputeWorkGroupSize[index];
1973 break;
1974 default:
1975 mState.getIntegeri_v(target, index, data);
1976 }
1977 }
1978 else
1979 {
1980 CastIndexedStateValues(this, nativeType, target, index, numParams, data);
1981 }
1982}
1983

1992
1993void Context::getInteger64i_v(GLenum target, GLuint index, GLint64 *data)
1994{
1995 // Queries about context capabilities and maximums are answered by Context.
1996 // Queries about current GL state values are answered by State.
1997
1998 GLenum nativeType;
1999 unsigned int numParams;
2000 bool queryStatus = getIndexedQueryParameterInfo(target, &nativeType, &numParams);
2001 ASSERT(queryStatus);
2002
2003 if (nativeType == GL_INT_64_ANGLEX)
2004 {
2005 mState.getInteger64i_v(target, index, data);
2006 }
2007 else
2008 {
2009 CastIndexedStateValues(this, nativeType, target, index, numParams, data);
2010 }
2011}
2012
2013void Context::getInteger64i_vRobust(GLenum target,
2014 GLuint index,
2015 GLsizei bufSize,
2016 GLsizei *length,
2017 GLint64 *data)
2018{
2019 getInteger64i_v(target, index, data);
2020}

2282void Context::drawArraysInstanced(PrimitiveMode mode,
2283 GLint first,
2284 GLsizei count,
2285 GLsizei instanceCount)
2286{
2287 // No-op if count draws no primitives for given mode
2288 if (noopDrawInstanced(mode, count, instanceCount))
2289 {
2290 return;
2291 }
2292
2293 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDraw(mode));
2294 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(
2295 mImplementation->drawArraysInstanced(this, mode, first, count, instanceCount));
2296 MarkTransformFeedbackBufferUsage(this, count, instanceCount);
2297 MarkShaderStorageUsage(this);
2298}

2433 }
2434 else
2435 {
2436 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->pushGroupMarker(length, marker));
2437 }

2535// Get one of the recorded errors and clear its flag, if any.
2536// [OpenGL ES 2.0.24] section 2.5 page 13.
2537GLenum Context::getError()
2538{
2539 if (mErrors.empty())
2540 {
2541 return GL_NO_ERROR;
2542 }
2543 else
2544 {
2545 return mErrors.popError();
2546 }
2547}
2548
2549// NOTE: this function should not assume that this context is current!
2550void Context::markContextLost(GraphicsResetStatus status)
2551{
2552 ASSERT(status != GraphicsResetStatus::NoError);
2553 if (mResetStrategy == GL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET_EXT)
2554 {
2555 mResetStatus = status;
2556 mContextLostForced = true;
2557 }
2558 setContextLost();
2559}
2560
2561void Context::setContextLost()
2562{
2563 mContextLost = true;
2564
2565 // Stop skipping validation, since many implementation entrypoint assume they can't
2566 // be called when lost, or with null object arguments, etc.
2567 mSkipValidation = false;
2568
2569 // Make sure we update TLS.
2570 gCurrentValidContext = nullptr;
2571}
2572
2573GLenum Context::getGraphicsResetStatus()
2574{
2575 // Even if the application doesn't want to know about resets, we want to know
2576 // as it will allow us to skip all the calls.
2577 if (mResetStrategy == GL_NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION_EXT)
2578 {
2579 if (!isContextLost() && mImplementation->getResetStatus() != GraphicsResetStatus::NoError)
2580 {
2581 setContextLost();
2582 }
2583
2584 // EXT_robustness, section 2.6: If the reset notification behavior is
2585 // NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION_EXT, then the implementation will never deliver notification of
2586 // reset events, and GetGraphicsResetStatusEXT will always return NO_ERROR.
2587 return GL_NO_ERROR;
2588 }
2589
2590 // The GL_EXT_robustness spec says that if a reset is encountered, a reset
2591 // status should be returned at least once, and GL_NO_ERROR should be returned
2592 // once the device has finished resetting.
2593 if (!isContextLost())
2594 {
2595 ASSERT(mResetStatus == GraphicsResetStatus::NoError);
2596 mResetStatus = mImplementation->getResetStatus();
2597
2598 if (mResetStatus != GraphicsResetStatus::NoError)
2599 {
2600 setContextLost();
2601 }
2602 }
2603 else if (!mContextLostForced && mResetStatus != GraphicsResetStatus::NoError)
2604 {
2605 // If markContextLost was used to mark the context lost then
2606 // assume that is not recoverable, and continue to report the
2607 // lost reset status for the lifetime of this context.
2608 mResetStatus = mImplementation->getResetStatus();
2609 }
2610
2611 return ToGLenum(mResetStatus);
2612}
2613
2614bool Context::isResetNotificationEnabled()
2615{
2616 return (mResetStrategy == GL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET_EXT);
2617}

2619const egl::Config *Context::getConfig() const
2620{
2621 return mConfig;
2622}

2624EGLenum Context::getClientType() const

2626 return mState.getClientType();
2627}
2628
2629EGLenum Context::getRenderBuffer() const
2630{
2631 const Framebuffer *framebuffer =
2632 mState.mFramebufferManager->getFramebuffer(Framebuffer::kDefaultDrawFramebufferHandle);
2633 if (framebuffer == nullptr)
2634 {
2635 return EGL_NONE;
2636 }
2637
2638 const FramebufferAttachment *backAttachment = framebuffer->getAttachment(this, GL_BACK);
2639 ASSERT(backAttachment != nullptr);
2640 return backAttachment->getSurface()->getRenderBuffer();
2641}
2642
2643VertexArray *Context::checkVertexArrayAllocation(VertexArrayID vertexArrayHandle)
2644{
2645 // Only called after a prior call to Gen.
2646 VertexArray *vertexArray = getVertexArray(vertexArrayHandle);
2647 if (!vertexArray)
2648 {
2649 vertexArray =
2650 new VertexArray(mImplementation.get(), vertexArrayHandle,
2651 mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttributes, mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttribBindings);
2652 vertexArray->setBufferAccessValidationEnabled(mBufferAccessValidationEnabled);
2653
2654 mVertexArrayMap.assign(vertexArrayHandle, vertexArray);
2655 }
2656
2657 return vertexArray;
2658}
2659
2660TransformFeedback *Context::checkTransformFeedbackAllocation(
2661 TransformFeedbackID transformFeedbackHandle)
2662{
2663 // Only called after a prior call to Gen.
2664 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = getTransformFeedback(transformFeedbackHandle);
2665 if (!transformFeedback)
2666 {
2667 transformFeedback =
2668 new TransformFeedback(mImplementation.get(), transformFeedbackHandle, mState.mCaps);
2669 transformFeedback->addRef();
2670 mTransformFeedbackMap.assign(transformFeedbackHandle, transformFeedback);
2671 }
2672
2673 return transformFeedback;
2674}
2675
2676bool Context::isVertexArrayGenerated(VertexArrayID vertexArray) const
2677{
2678 ASSERT(mVertexArrayMap.contains({0}));
2679 return mVertexArrayMap.contains(vertexArray);
2680}
2681
2682bool Context::isTransformFeedbackGenerated(TransformFeedbackID transformFeedback) const
2683{
2684 ASSERT(mTransformFeedbackMap.contains({0}));
2685 return mTransformFeedbackMap.contains(transformFeedback);
2686}
2687
2688void Context::detachTexture(TextureID texture)
2689{
2690 // The State cannot unbind image observers itself, they are owned by the Context
2691 Texture *tex = mState.mTextureManager->getTexture(texture);
2692 for (auto &imageBinding : mImageObserverBindings)
2693 {
2694 if (imageBinding.getSubject() == tex)
2695 {
2696 imageBinding.reset();
2697 }
2698 }
2699
2700 // Simple pass-through to State's detachTexture method, as textures do not require
2701 // allocation map management either here or in the resource manager at detach time.
2702 // Zero textures are held by the Context, and we don't attempt to request them from
2703 // the State.
2704 mState.detachTexture(this, mZeroTextures, texture);
2705}
2706
2707void Context::detachBuffer(Buffer *buffer)
2708{
2709 // Simple pass-through to State's detachBuffer method, since
2710 // only buffer attachments to container objects that are bound to the current context
2711 // should be detached. And all those are available in State.
2712
2713 // [OpenGL ES 3.2] section 5.1.2 page 45:
2714 // Attachments to unbound container objects, such as
2715 // deletion of a buffer attached to a vertex array object which is not bound to the context,
2716 // are not affected and continue to act as references on the deleted object
2717 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.detachBuffer(this, buffer));
2718}
2719
2720void Context::detachFramebuffer(FramebufferID framebuffer)
2721{
2722 // Framebuffer detachment is handled by Context, because 0 is a valid
2723 // Framebuffer object, and a pointer to it must be passed from Context
2724 // to State at binding time.
2725
2726 // [OpenGL ES 2.0.24] section 4.4 page 107:
2727 // If a framebuffer that is currently bound to the target FRAMEBUFFER is deleted, it is as
2728 // though BindFramebuffer had been executed with the target of FRAMEBUFFER and framebuffer of
2729 // zero.
2730
2731 if (mState.removeReadFramebufferBinding(framebuffer) && framebuffer.value != 0)
2732 {
2733 bindReadFramebuffer({0});
2734 }
2735
2736 if (mState.removeDrawFramebufferBinding(framebuffer) && framebuffer.value != 0)
2737 {
2738 bindDrawFramebuffer({0});
2739 }
2740}
2741
2742void Context::detachRenderbuffer(RenderbufferID renderbuffer)
2743{
2744 mState.detachRenderbuffer(this, renderbuffer);
2745}
2746
2747void Context::detachVertexArray(VertexArrayID vertexArray)
2748{
2749 // Vertex array detachment is handled by Context, because 0 is a valid
2750 // VAO, and a pointer to it must be passed from Context to State at
2751 // binding time.
2752
2753 // [OpenGL ES 3.0.2] section 2.10 page 43:
2754 // If a vertex array object that is currently bound is deleted, the binding
2755 // for that object reverts to zero and the default vertex array becomes current.
2756 if (mState.removeVertexArrayBinding(this, vertexArray))
2757 {
2758 bindVertexArray({0});
2759 }
2760}
2761
2762void Context::detachTransformFeedback(TransformFeedbackID transformFeedback)
2763{
2764 // Transform feedback detachment is handled by Context, because 0 is a valid
2765 // transform feedback, and a pointer to it must be passed from Context to State at
2766 // binding time.
2767
2768 // The OpenGL specification doesn't mention what should happen when the currently bound
2769 // transform feedback object is deleted. Since it is a container object, we treat it like
2770 // VAOs and FBOs and set the current bound transform feedback back to 0.
2771 if (mState.removeTransformFeedbackBinding(this, transformFeedback))
2772 {
2773 bindTransformFeedback(GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK, {0});
2774 }
2775}

2937void Context::initRendererString()
2938{
2939 std::ostringstream rendererString;
2940 rendererString << "ANGLE (";
2941 rendererString << mImplementation->getRendererDescription();
2942 rendererString << ")";
2943
2944 mRendererString = MakeStaticString(rendererString.str());
2945}
2946
2947void Context::initVersionStrings()
2948{
2949 const Version &clientVersion = getClientVersion();
2950
2951 std::ostringstream versionString;
2952 if (getClientType() == EGL_OPENGL_ES_API)
2953 {
2954 versionString << "OpenGL ES ";
2955 }
2956 versionString << clientVersion.major << "." << clientVersion.minor << ".0 (ANGLE "
2957 << ANGLE_VERSION_STRING << ")";
2958 mVersionString = MakeStaticString(versionString.str());
2959
2960 std::ostringstream shadingLanguageVersionString;
2961 if (getClientType() == EGL_OPENGL_ES_API)
2962 {
2963 shadingLanguageVersionString << "OpenGL ES GLSL ES ";
2964 }
2965 else
2966 {
2967 ASSERT(getClientType() == EGL_OPENGL_API);
2968 shadingLanguageVersionString << "OpenGL GLSL ";
2969 }
2970 shadingLanguageVersionString << (clientVersion.major == 2 ? 1 : clientVersion.major) << "."
2971 << clientVersion.minor << "0 (ANGLE " << ANGLE_VERSION_STRING
2972 << ")";
2973 mShadingLanguageString = MakeStaticString(shadingLanguageVersionString.str());
2974}
2975
2976void Context::initExtensionStrings()
2977{
2978 auto mergeExtensionStrings = [](const std::vector<const char *> &strings) {
2979 std::ostringstream combinedStringStream;
2980 std::copy(strings.begin(), strings.end(),
2981 std::ostream_iterator<const char *>(combinedStringStream, " "));
2982 return MakeStaticString(combinedStringStream.str());
2983 };
2984
2985 mExtensionStrings.clear();
2986 for (const auto &extensionString : mState.mExtensions.getStrings())
2987 {
2988 mExtensionStrings.push_back(MakeStaticString(extensionString));
2989 }
2990 mExtensionString = mergeExtensionStrings(mExtensionStrings);
2991
2992 mRequestableExtensionStrings.clear();
2993 for (const auto &extensionInfo : GetExtensionInfoMap())
2994 {
2995 if (extensionInfo.second.Requestable &&
2996 !(mState.mExtensions.*(extensionInfo.second.ExtensionsMember)) &&
2997 mSupportedExtensions.*(extensionInfo.second.ExtensionsMember))
2998 {
2999 mRequestableExtensionStrings.push_back(MakeStaticString(extensionInfo.first));
3000 }
3001 }
3002 mRequestableExtensionString = mergeExtensionStrings(mRequestableExtensionStrings);
3003}
