3005const GLubyte *Context::getString(GLenum name)
3006{
3007 return static_cast<const Context *>(this)->getString(name);
3008}
3009
3010const GLubyte *Context::getStringi(GLenum name, GLuint index)
3011{
3012 return static_cast<const Context *>(this)->getStringi(name, index);
3013}
3014
3015const GLubyte *Context::getString(GLenum name) const
3016{
3017 switch (name)
3018 {
3019 case GL_VENDOR:
3020 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>("Google Inc.");
3021
3022 case GL_RENDERER:
3023 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mRendererString);
3024
3025 case GL_VERSION:
3026 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mVersionString);
3027
3028 case GL_SHADING_LANGUAGE_VERSION:
3029 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mShadingLanguageString);
3030
3031 case GL_EXTENSIONS:
3032 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mExtensionString);
3033
3034 case GL_REQUESTABLE_EXTENSIONS_ANGLE:
3035 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mRequestableExtensionString);
3036
3037 default:
3038 UNREACHABLE();
3039 return nullptr;
3040 }
3041}
3042
3043const GLubyte *Context::getStringi(GLenum name, GLuint index) const
3044{
3045 switch (name)
3046 {
3047 case GL_EXTENSIONS:
3048 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mExtensionStrings[index]);
3049
3050 case GL_REQUESTABLE_EXTENSIONS_ANGLE:
3051 return reinterpret_cast<const GLubyte *>(mRequestableExtensionStrings[index]);
3052
3053 default:
3054 UNREACHABLE();
3055 return nullptr;
3056 }
3057}
3058
3059size_t Context::getExtensionStringCount() const
3060{
3061 return mExtensionStrings.size();
3062}
3063
3064bool Context::isExtensionRequestable(const char *name) const
3065{
3066 const ExtensionInfoMap &extensionInfos = GetExtensionInfoMap();
3067 auto extension = extensionInfos.find(name);
3068
3069 return extension != extensionInfos.end() && extension->second.Requestable &&
3070 mSupportedExtensions.*(extension->second.ExtensionsMember);
3071}
3072
3073bool Context::isExtensionDisablable(const char *name) const
3074{
3075 const ExtensionInfoMap &extensionInfos = GetExtensionInfoMap();
3076 auto extension = extensionInfos.find(name);
3077
3078 return extension != extensionInfos.end() && extension->second.Disablable &&
3079 mSupportedExtensions.*(extension->second.ExtensionsMember);
3080}
3081
3082void Context::requestExtension(const char *name)
3083{
3084 setExtensionEnabled(name, true);
3085}
3086void Context::disableExtension(const char *name)
3087{
3088 setExtensionEnabled(name, false);
3089}
3090
3091void Context::setExtensionEnabled(const char *name, bool enabled)
3092{
3093 // OVR_multiview is implicitly enabled when OVR_multiview2 is enabled
3094 if (strcmp(name, "GL_OVR_multiview2") == 0)
3095 {
3096 setExtensionEnabled("GL_OVR_multiview", enabled);
3097 }
3098 const ExtensionInfoMap &extensionInfos = GetExtensionInfoMap();
3099 ASSERT(extensionInfos.find(name) != extensionInfos.end());
3100 const auto &extension = extensionInfos.at(name);
3101 ASSERT(extension.Requestable);
3102 ASSERT(isExtensionRequestable(name));
3103
3104 if (mState.mExtensions.*(extension.ExtensionsMember) == enabled)
3105 {
3106 // No change
3107 return;
3108 }
3109
3110 mState.mExtensions.*(extension.ExtensionsMember) = enabled;
3111
3112 reinitializeAfterExtensionsChanged();
3113}
3114
3115void Context::reinitializeAfterExtensionsChanged()
3116{
3117 updateCaps();
3118 initExtensionStrings();
3119
3120 // Release the shader compiler so it will be re-created with the requested extensions enabled.
3121 releaseShaderCompiler();
3122
3123 // Invalidate all textures and framebuffer. Some extensions make new formats renderable or
3124 // sampleable.
3125 mState.mTextureManager->signalAllTexturesDirty();
3126 for (auto &zeroTexture : mZeroTextures)
3127 {
3128 if (zeroTexture.get() != nullptr)
3129 {
3130 zeroTexture->signalDirtyStorage(InitState::Initialized);
3131 }
3132 }
3133
3134 mState.mFramebufferManager->invalidateFramebufferCompletenessCache();
3135}
3136
3137size_t Context::getRequestableExtensionStringCount() const
3138{
3139 return mRequestableExtensionStrings.size();
3140}
3141
3142void Context::beginTransformFeedback(PrimitiveMode primitiveMode)
3143{
3144 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
3145 ASSERT(transformFeedback != nullptr);
3146 ASSERT(!transformFeedback->isPaused());
3147
3148 // TODO: http://anglebug.com/3570: Handle PPOs
3149 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(transformFeedback->begin(this, primitiveMode, mState.getProgram()));
3150 mStateCache.onActiveTransformFeedbackChange(this);
3151}
3152
3153bool Context::hasActiveTransformFeedback(ShaderProgramID program) const
3154{
3155 for (auto pair : mTransformFeedbackMap)
3156 {
3157 if (pair.second != nullptr && pair.second->hasBoundProgram(program))
3158 {
3159 return true;
3160 }
3161 }
3162 return false;
3163}
3164
3165Extensions Context::generateSupportedExtensions() const
3166{
3167 Extensions supportedExtensions = mImplementation->getNativeExtensions();
3168
3169 // Explicitly enable GL_KHR_parallel_shader_compile
3170 supportedExtensions.parallelShaderCompile = true;
3171
3172 if (getClientVersion() < ES_2_0)
3173 {
3174 // Default extensions for GLES1
3175 supportedExtensions.pointSizeArrayOES = true;
3176 supportedExtensions.textureCubeMapOES = true;
3177 supportedExtensions.pointSpriteOES = true;
3178 supportedExtensions.drawTextureOES = true;
3179 supportedExtensions.parallelShaderCompile = false;
3180 supportedExtensions.texture3DOES = false;
3181 }
3182
3183 if (getClientVersion() < ES_3_0)
3184 {
3185 // Disable ES3+ extensions
3186 supportedExtensions.colorBufferFloat = false;
3187 supportedExtensions.eglImageExternalEssl3OES = false;
3188 supportedExtensions.textureNorm16 = false;
3189 supportedExtensions.multiview = false;
3190 supportedExtensions.multiview2 = false;
3191 supportedExtensions.maxViews = 1u;
3192 supportedExtensions.copyTexture3d = false;
3193 supportedExtensions.textureMultisample = false;
3194 supportedExtensions.drawBuffersIndexedEXT = false;
3195 supportedExtensions.drawBuffersIndexedOES = false;
3196 supportedExtensions.eglImageArray = false;
3197 supportedExtensions.textureSRGBOverride = false;
3198
3199 // Requires glCompressedTexImage3D
3200 supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCOES = false;
3201
3202 // Don't expose GL_EXT_texture_sRGB_decode without sRGB texture support
3203 if (!supportedExtensions.sRGB)
3204 {
3205 supportedExtensions.textureSRGBDecode = false;
3206 }
3207
3208 // Don't expose GL_OES_texture_float_linear without full legacy float texture support
3209 // The renderer may report OES_texture_float_linear without OES_texture_float
3210 // This is valid in a GLES 3.0 context, but not in a GLES 2.0 context
3211 if (!(supportedExtensions.textureFloatOES && supportedExtensions.textureHalfFloat))
3212 {
3213 supportedExtensions.textureFloatLinearOES = false;
3214 supportedExtensions.textureHalfFloatLinear = false;
3215 }
3216
3217 // Because of the difference in the SNORM to FLOAT conversion formula
3218 // between GLES 2.0 and 3.0, vertex type 10_10_10_2 is disabled
3219 // when the context version is lower than 3.0
3220 supportedExtensions.vertexAttribType1010102OES = false;
3221 }
3222
3223 if (getClientVersion() < ES_3_1)
3224 {
3225 // Disable ES3.1+ extensions
3226 supportedExtensions.geometryShader = false;
3227
3228 // TODO(http://anglebug.com/2775): Multisample arrays could be supported on ES 3.0 as well
3229 // once 2D multisample texture extension is exposed there.
3230 supportedExtensions.textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES = false;
3231 }
3232
3233 if (getClientVersion() > ES_2_0)
3234 {
3235 // FIXME(geofflang): Don't support EXT_sRGB in non-ES2 contexts
3236 // supportedExtensions.sRGB = false;
3237
3238 // If colorBufferFloat is disabled but colorBufferHalfFloat is enabled, then we will expose
3239 // some floating-point formats as color buffer targets but reject blits between fixed-point
3240 // and floating-point formats (this behavior is only enabled in colorBufferFloat, and must
3241 // be rejected if only colorBufferHalfFloat is enabled).
3242 // dEQP does not check for this, and will assume that floating-point and fixed-point formats
3243 // can be blit onto each other if the format is available.
3244 // We require colorBufferFloat to be present in order to enable colorBufferHalfFloat, so
3245 // that blitting is always allowed if the requested formats are exposed and have the correct
3246 // feature capabilities.
3247 // WebGL 2 wants to support colorBufferHalfFloat without colorBufferFloat.
3248 if (!supportedExtensions.colorBufferFloat && !mWebGLContext)
3249 {
3250 supportedExtensions.colorBufferHalfFloat = false;
3251 }
3252
3253 // Disable support for CHROMIUM_color_buffer_float_rgb[a] in ES 3.0+, these extensions are
3254 // non-conformant in ES 3.0 and superseded by EXT_color_buffer_float.
3255 supportedExtensions.colorBufferFloatRGB = false;
3256 supportedExtensions.colorBufferFloatRGBA = false;
3257 }
3258
3259 if (getFrontendFeatures().disableAnisotropicFiltering.enabled)
3260 {
3261 supportedExtensions.textureFilterAnisotropic = false;
3262 }
3263
3264 // Some extensions are always available because they are implemented in the GL layer.
3265 supportedExtensions.bindUniformLocation = true;
3266 supportedExtensions.vertexArrayObjectOES = true;
3267 supportedExtensions.bindGeneratesResource = true;
3268 supportedExtensions.clientArrays = true;
3269 supportedExtensions.requestExtension = true;
3270 supportedExtensions.multiDraw = true;
3271
3272 // Enable the no error extension if the context was created with the flag.
3273 supportedExtensions.noError = mSkipValidation;
3274
3275 // Enable surfaceless to advertise we'll have the correct behavior when there is no default FBO
3276 supportedExtensions.surfacelessContextOES = mSurfacelessSupported;
3277
3278 // Explicitly enable GL_KHR_debug
3279 supportedExtensions.debug = true;
3280 supportedExtensions.maxDebugMessageLength = 1024;
3281 supportedExtensions.maxDebugLoggedMessages = 1024;
3282 supportedExtensions.maxDebugGroupStackDepth = 1024;
3283 supportedExtensions.maxLabelLength = 1024;
3284
3285 // Explicitly enable GL_ANGLE_robust_client_memory if the context supports validation.
3286 supportedExtensions.robustClientMemory = !mSkipValidation;
3287
3288 // Determine robust resource init availability from EGL.
3289 supportedExtensions.robustResourceInitialization = mState.isRobustResourceInitEnabled();
3290
3291 // mState.mExtensions.robustBufferAccessBehavior is true only if robust access is true and the
3292 // backend supports it.
3293 supportedExtensions.robustBufferAccessBehavior =
3294 mRobustAccess && supportedExtensions.robustBufferAccessBehavior;
3295
3296 // Enable the cache control query unconditionally.
3297 supportedExtensions.programCacheControl = true;
3298
3299 // Enable EGL_ANGLE_explicit_context subextensions
3300 if (mExplicitContextAvailable)
3301 {
3302 // GL_ANGLE_explicit_context_gles1
3303 supportedExtensions.explicitContextGles1 = true;
3304 // GL_ANGLE_explicit_context
3305 supportedExtensions.explicitContext = true;
3306 }
3307
3308 // If EGL_KHR_fence_sync is not enabled, don't expose GL_OES_EGL_sync.
3309 ASSERT(mDisplay);
3310 if (!mDisplay->getExtensions().fenceSync)
3311 {
3312 supportedExtensions.eglSyncOES = false;
3313 }
3314
3315 if (mDisplay->getExtensions().robustnessVideoMemoryPurgeNV)
3316 {
3317 supportedExtensions.robustnessVideoMemoryPurgeNV = true;
3318 }
3319
3320 supportedExtensions.memorySize = true;
3321
3322 // GL_CHROMIUM_lose_context is implemented in the frontend
3323 supportedExtensions.loseContextCHROMIUM = true;
3324
3325 // The ASTC texture extensions have dependency requirements.
3326 if (supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCHDRKHR ||
3327 supportedExtensions.textureCompressionSliced3dASTCKHR)
3328 {
3329 // GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_hdr cannot be exposed without also exposing
3330 // GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_ldr
3331 ASSERT(supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCLDRKHR);
3332 }
3333
3334 if (supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCOES)
3335 {
3336 // GL_OES_texture_compression_astc cannot be exposed without also exposing
3337 // GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_ldr and GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_hdr
3338 ASSERT(supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCLDRKHR);
3339 ASSERT(supportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCHDRKHR);
3340 }
3341
3342 // GL_ANGLE_get_tex_level_parameter is implemented in the frontend
3343 supportedExtensions.getTexLevelParameterANGLE = true;
3344
3345 return supportedExtensions;
3346}
3347
3348void Context::initCaps()
3349{
3350 mState.mCaps = mImplementation->getNativeCaps();
3351
3352 mSupportedExtensions = generateSupportedExtensions();
3353
3354 if (!mDisplay->getFrontendFeatures().allowCompressedFormats.enabled)
3355 {
3356 INFO() << "Limiting compressed format support.\n";
3357
3358 mSupportedExtensions.compressedEACR11SignedTextureOES = false;
3359 mSupportedExtensions.compressedEACR11UnsignedTextureOES = false;
3360 mSupportedExtensions.compressedEACRG11SignedTextureOES = false;
3361 mSupportedExtensions.compressedEACRG11UnsignedTextureOES = false;
3362 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC1RGB8SubTexture = false;
3363 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC1RGB8TextureOES = false;
3364 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2PunchthroughARGB8TextureOES = false;
3365 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2PunchthroughAsRGB8AlphaTextureOES = false;
3366 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2RGB8TextureOES = false;
3367 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2RGBA8TextureOES = false;
3368 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2sRGB8Alpha8TextureOES = false;
3369 mSupportedExtensions.compressedETC2sRGB8TextureOES = false;
3370 mSupportedExtensions.compressedTextureETC = false;
3371 mSupportedExtensions.compressedTexturePVRTC = false;
3372 mSupportedExtensions.compressedTexturePVRTCsRGB = false;
3373 mSupportedExtensions.copyCompressedTexture = false;
3374 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCHDRKHR = false;
3375 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCLDRKHR = false;
3376 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionASTCOES = false;
3377 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionBPTC = false;
3378 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionDXT1 = false;
3379 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionDXT3 = false;
3380 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionDXT5 = false;
3381 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionRGTC = false;
3382 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionS3TCsRGB = false;
3383 mSupportedExtensions.textureCompressionSliced3dASTCKHR = false;
3384 mSupportedExtensions.textureFilteringCHROMIUM = false;
3385
3386 mState.mCaps.compressedTextureFormats.clear();
3387 }
3388
3389 mState.mExtensions = mSupportedExtensions;
3390
3391 mState.mLimitations = mImplementation->getNativeLimitations();
3392
3393 // GLES1 emulation: Initialize caps (Table 6.20 / 6.22 in the ES 1.1 spec)
3394 if (getClientType() == EGL_OPENGL_API || getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0))
3395 {
3396 mState.mCaps.maxMultitextureUnits = 4;
3397 mState.mCaps.maxClipPlanes = 6;
3398 mState.mCaps.maxLights = 8;
3399 mState.mCaps.maxModelviewMatrixStackDepth = Caps::GlobalMatrixStackDepth;
3400 mState.mCaps.maxProjectionMatrixStackDepth = Caps::GlobalMatrixStackDepth;
3401 mState.mCaps.maxTextureMatrixStackDepth = Caps::GlobalMatrixStackDepth;
3402 mState.mCaps.minSmoothPointSize = 1.0f;
3403 mState.mCaps.maxSmoothPointSize = 1.0f;
3404 mState.mCaps.minSmoothLineWidth = 1.0f;
3405 mState.mCaps.maxSmoothLineWidth = 1.0f;
3406 }
3407
3408#if 0
3409// This logging can generate a lot of spam in test suites that create many contexts
3410# define ANGLE_LOG_LIMITED_CAP(cap, limit) \
3411 INFO() << "Limiting " << #cap << " to implementation limit " << (limit) << " (was " \
3412 << (cap) << ")."
3413#else
3414# define ANGLE_LOG_LIMITED_CAP(cap, limit)
3415#endif
3416
3417#define ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(cap, limit) \
3418 do \
3419 { \
3420 if ((cap) > (limit)) \
3421 { \
3422 ANGLE_LOG_LIMITED_CAP(cap, limit); \
3423 (cap) = (limit); \
3424 } \
3425 } while (0)
3426
3427 // Apply/Verify implementation limits
3428 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttributes, MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS);
3429 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttribStride,
3430 static_cast<GLint>(limits::kMaxVertexAttribStride));
3431
3432 ASSERT(mState.mCaps.minAliasedPointSize >= 1.0f);
3433
3434 if (getClientVersion() < ES_3_1)
3435 {
3436 mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttribBindings = mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttributes;
3437 }
3438 else
3439 {
3440 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxVertexAttribBindings, MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIB_BINDINGS);
3441 }
3442
3443 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.max2DTextureSize, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_2D_TEXTURE_SIZE);
3444 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCubeMapTextureSize, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_CUBE_MAP_TEXTURE_SIZE);
3445 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.max3DTextureSize, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_3D_TEXTURE_SIZE);
3446 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxArrayTextureLayers, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_2D_ARRAY_TEXTURE_LAYERS);
3447 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxRectangleTextureSize, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_2D_TEXTURE_SIZE);
3448
3449 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformBlocks[ShaderType::Vertex],
3450 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_VERTEX_SHADER_UNIFORM_BUFFERS);
3451 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformBlocks[ShaderType::Geometry],
3452 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_GEOMETRY_SHADER_UNIFORM_BUFFERS);
3453 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformBlocks[ShaderType::Fragment],
3454 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_FRAGMENT_SHADER_UNIFORM_BUFFERS);
3455 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderUniformBlocks[ShaderType::Compute],
3456 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_COMPUTE_SHADER_UNIFORM_BUFFERS);
3457 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCombinedUniformBlocks,
3458 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_UNIFORM_BUFFERS);
3459 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxUniformBufferBindings,
3460 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDINGS);
3461
3462 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxVertexOutputComponents, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_VARYING_VECTORS * 4);
3463 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxFragmentInputComponents,
3464 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_VARYING_VECTORS * 4);
3465
3466 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxTransformFeedbackInterleavedComponents,
3467 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_INTERLEAVED_COMPONENTS);
3468 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxTransformFeedbackSeparateAttributes,
3469 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_SEPARATE_ATTRIBS);
3470 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxTransformFeedbackSeparateComponents,
3471 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_SEPARATE_COMPONENTS);
3472
3473 // Limit textures as well, so we can use fast bitsets with texture bindings.
3474 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCombinedTextureImageUnits, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_ACTIVE_TEXTURES);
3475 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
3476 {
3477 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderTextureImageUnits[shaderType],
3478 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_SHADER_TEXTURES);
3479 }
3480
3481 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxImageUnits, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_IMAGE_UNITS);
3482 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCombinedImageUniforms, IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_IMAGE_UNITS);
3483 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
3484 {
3485 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderImageUniforms[shaderType],
3486 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_IMAGE_UNITS);
3487 }
3488
3489 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
3490 {
3491 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderAtomicCounterBuffers[shaderType],
3492 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFERS);
3493 }
3494 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCombinedAtomicCounterBuffers,
3495 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFERS);
3496
3497 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
3498 {
3499 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderStorageBlocks[shaderType],
3500 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDINGS);
3501 }
3502 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxShaderStorageBufferBindings,
3503 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDINGS);
3504 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxCombinedShaderStorageBlocks,
3505 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDINGS);
3506
3507 ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP(mState.mCaps.maxSampleMaskWords, MAX_SAMPLE_MASK_WORDS);
3508
3509#undef ANGLE_LIMIT_CAP
3510#undef ANGLE_LOG_CAP_LIMIT
3511
3512 // WebGL compatibility
3513 mState.mExtensions.webglCompatibility = mWebGLContext;
3514 for (const auto &extensionInfo : GetExtensionInfoMap())
3515 {
3516 // If the user has requested that extensions start disabled and they are requestable,
3517 // disable them.
3518 if (!mExtensionsEnabled && extensionInfo.second.Requestable)
3519 {
3520 mState.mExtensions.*(extensionInfo.second.ExtensionsMember) = false;
3521 }
3522 }
3523
3524 // If we're capturing application calls for replay, don't expose any binary formats to prevent
3525 // traces from trying to use cached results
3526 if (getFrameCapture()->enabled())
3527 {
3528 INFO() << "Limiting binary format support count to zero while FrameCapture enabled"
3529 << std::endl;
3530 mDisplay->overrideFrontendFeatures({"disable_program_binary"}, true);
3531
3532 INFO() << "Disabling GL_EXT_map_buffer_range and GL_OES_mapbuffer during capture, which "
3533 "are not supported on some native drivers"
3534 << std::endl;
3535 mState.mExtensions.mapBufferRange = false;
3536 mState.mExtensions.mapBufferOES = false;
3537 }
3538
3539 // Disable support for OES_get_program_binary
3540 if (mDisplay->getFrontendFeatures().disableProgramBinary.enabled)
3541 {
3542 mState.mExtensions.getProgramBinaryOES = false;
3543 mState.mCaps.shaderBinaryFormats.clear();
3544 mState.mCaps.programBinaryFormats.clear();
3545 }
3546
3547 // Generate texture caps
3548 updateCaps();
3549}
3550
3551void Context::updateCaps()
3552{
3553 mState.mCaps.compressedTextureFormats.clear();
3554 mState.mTextureCaps.clear();
3555
3556 for (GLenum sizedInternalFormat : GetAllSizedInternalFormats())
3557 {
3558 TextureCaps formatCaps = mImplementation->getNativeTextureCaps().get(sizedInternalFormat);
3559 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(sizedInternalFormat);
3560
3561 // Update the format caps based on the client version and extensions.
3562 // Caps are AND'd with the renderer caps because some core formats are still unsupported in
3563 // ES3.
3564 formatCaps.texturable = formatCaps.texturable &&
3565 formatInfo.textureSupport(getClientVersion(), mState.mExtensions);
3566 formatCaps.filterable = formatCaps.filterable &&
3567 formatInfo.filterSupport(getClientVersion(), mState.mExtensions);
3568 formatCaps.textureAttachment =
3569 formatCaps.textureAttachment &&
3570 formatInfo.textureAttachmentSupport(getClientVersion(), mState.mExtensions);
3571 formatCaps.renderbuffer =
3572 formatCaps.renderbuffer &&
3573 formatInfo.renderbufferSupport(getClientVersion(), mState.mExtensions);
3574 formatCaps.blendable =
3575 formatCaps.blendable && formatInfo.blendSupport(getClientVersion(), mState.mExtensions);
3576
3577 // OpenGL ES does not support multisampling with non-rendererable formats
3578 // OpenGL ES 3.0 or prior does not support multisampling with integer formats
3579 if (!formatCaps.renderbuffer ||
3580 (getClientVersion() < ES_3_1 && !mSupportedExtensions.textureMultisample &&
3581 formatInfo.isInt()))
3582 {
3583 formatCaps.sampleCounts.clear();
3584 }
3585 else
3586 {
3587 // We may have limited the max samples for some required renderbuffer formats due to
3588 // non-conformant formats. In this case MAX_SAMPLES needs to be lowered accordingly.
3589 GLuint formatMaxSamples = formatCaps.getMaxSamples();
3590
3591 // GLES 3.0.5 section 4.4.2.2: "Implementations must support creation of renderbuffers
3592 // in these required formats with up to the value of MAX_SAMPLES multisamples, with the
3593 // exception of signed and unsigned integer formats."
3594 if (!formatInfo.isInt() && formatInfo.isRequiredRenderbufferFormat(getClientVersion()))
3595 {
3596 ASSERT(getClientVersion() < ES_3_0 || formatMaxSamples >= 4);
3597 mState.mCaps.maxSamples =
3598 std::min(static_cast<GLuint>(mState.mCaps.maxSamples), formatMaxSamples);
3599 }
3600
3601 // Handle GLES 3.1 MAX_*_SAMPLES values similarly to MAX_SAMPLES.
3602 if (getClientVersion() >= ES_3_1 || mSupportedExtensions.textureMultisample)
3603 {
3604 // GLES 3.1 section 9.2.5: "Implementations must support creation of renderbuffers
3605 // in these required formats with up to the value of MAX_SAMPLES multisamples, with
3606 // the exception that the signed and unsigned integer formats are required only to
3607 // support creation of renderbuffers with up to the value of MAX_INTEGER_SAMPLES
3608 // multisamples, which must be at least one."
3609 if (formatInfo.isInt())
3610 {
3611 mState.mCaps.maxIntegerSamples = std::min(
3612 static_cast<GLuint>(mState.mCaps.maxIntegerSamples), formatMaxSamples);
3613 }
3614
3615 // GLES 3.1 section 19.3.1.
3616 if (formatCaps.texturable)
3617 {
3618 if (formatInfo.depthBits > 0)
3619 {
3620 mState.mCaps.maxDepthTextureSamples =
3621 std::min(static_cast<GLuint>(mState.mCaps.maxDepthTextureSamples),
3622 formatMaxSamples);
3623 }
3624 else if (formatInfo.redBits > 0)
3625 {
3626 mState.mCaps.maxColorTextureSamples =
3627 std::min(static_cast<GLuint>(mState.mCaps.maxColorTextureSamples),
3628 formatMaxSamples);
3629 }
3630 }
3631 }
3632 }
3633
3634 if (formatCaps.texturable && formatInfo.compressed)
3635 {
3636 mState.mCaps.compressedTextureFormats.push_back(sizedInternalFormat);
3637 }
3638
3639 mState.mTextureCaps.insert(sizedInternalFormat, formatCaps);
3640 }
3641
3642 // If program binary is disabled, blank out the memory cache pointer.
3643 if (!mSupportedExtensions.getProgramBinaryOES)
3644 {
3645 mMemoryProgramCache = nullptr;
3646 }
3647
3648 // Compute which buffer types are allowed
3649 mValidBufferBindings.reset();
3650 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::ElementArray);
3651 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::Array);
3652
3653 if (mState.mExtensions.pixelBufferObjectNV || getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0)
3654 {
3655 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::PixelPack);
3656 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::PixelUnpack);
3657 }
3658
3659 if (getClientVersion() >= ES_3_0)
3660 {
3661 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::CopyRead);
3662 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::CopyWrite);
3663 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::TransformFeedback);
3664 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::Uniform);
3665 }
3666
3667 if (getClientVersion() >= ES_3_1)
3668 {
3669 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::AtomicCounter);
3670 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::ShaderStorage);
3671 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::DrawIndirect);
3672 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::DispatchIndirect);
3673 }
3674
3675 if (getClientVersion() >= ES_3_2 || mState.mExtensions.textureBufferAny())
3676 {
3677 mValidBufferBindings.set(BufferBinding::Texture);
3678 }
3679
3680 mThreadPool = angle::WorkerThreadPool::Create(mState.mExtensions.parallelShaderCompile);
3681
3682 // Reinitialize some dirty bits that depend on extensions.
3683 if (mState.isRobustResourceInitEnabled())
3684 {
3685 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_DRAW_ATTACHMENTS);
3686 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_TEXTURES_INIT);
3687 mDrawDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_IMAGES_INIT);
3688 mBlitDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_DRAW_ATTACHMENTS);
3689 mBlitDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_ATTACHMENTS);
3690 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_TEXTURES_INIT);
3691 mComputeDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_IMAGES_INIT);
3692 mReadPixelsDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_ATTACHMENTS);
3693 mCopyImageDirtyBits.set(State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING);
3694 mCopyImageDirtyObjects.set(State::DIRTY_OBJECT_READ_ATTACHMENTS);
3695 }
3696
3697 // We need to validate buffer bounds if we are in a WebGL or robust access context and the
3698 // back-end does not support robust buffer access behaviour.
3699 mBufferAccessValidationEnabled =
3700 (!mSupportedExtensions.robustBufferAccessBehavior && (mState.isWebGL() || mRobustAccess));
3701
3702 // Cache this in the VertexArrays. They need to check it in state change notifications.
3703 for (auto vaoIter : mVertexArrayMap)
3704 {
3705 VertexArray *vao = vaoIter.second;
3706 vao->setBufferAccessValidationEnabled(mBufferAccessValidationEnabled);
3707 }
3708
3709 // Reinitialize state cache after extension changes.
3710 mStateCache.initialize(this);
3711}
3712
3713bool Context::noopDrawInstanced(PrimitiveMode mode, GLsizei count, GLsizei instanceCount) const
3714{
3715 return (instanceCount == 0) || noopDraw(mode, count);
3716}
3717
3718angle::Result Context::prepareForClear(GLbitfield mask)
3719{
3720 // Sync the draw framebuffer manually after the clear attachments.
3721 ANGLE_TRY(mState.getDrawFramebuffer()->ensureClearAttachmentsInitialized(this, mask));
3722 return syncStateForClear();
3723}
3724
3725angle::Result Context::prepareForClearBuffer(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer)
3726{
3727 // Sync the draw framebuffer manually after the clear attachments.
3728 ANGLE_TRY(mState.getDrawFramebuffer()->ensureClearBufferAttachmentsInitialized(this, buffer,
3729 drawbuffer));
3730 return syncStateForClear();
3731}
3732
3733ANGLE_INLINE angle::Result Context::prepareForCopyImage()
3734{
3735 ANGLE_TRY(syncDirtyObjects(mCopyImageDirtyObjects, Command::CopyImage));
3736 return syncDirtyBits(mCopyImageDirtyBits);
3737}
3738
3739ANGLE_INLINE angle::Result Context::prepareForDispatch()
3740{
3741 // We always assume PPOs are used for draws, until they aren't. If we are executing a dispatch
3742 // with a PPO, we need to convert it from a "draw"-type to "dispatch"-type.
3743 convertPpoToComputeOrDraw(true);
3744
3745 // Converting a PPO from graphics to compute requires re-linking it.
3746 // The compute shader must have successfully linked before being included in the PPO, so no link
3747 // errors that would have been caught during validation should be possible when re-linking the
3748 // PPO with the compute shader.
3749 Program *program = mState.getProgram();
3750 ProgramPipeline *pipeline = mState.getProgramPipeline();
3751 if (!program && pipeline)
3752 {
3753 bool goodResult = pipeline->link(this) == angle::Result::Continue;
3754 // Linking the PPO can't fail due to a validation error within the compute program,
3755 // since it successfully linked already in order to become part of the PPO in the first
3756 // place.
3757 ANGLE_CHECK(this, goodResult, "Program pipeline link failed", GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
3758 }
3759
3760 ANGLE_TRY(syncDirtyObjects(mComputeDirtyObjects, Command::Dispatch));
3761 return syncDirtyBits(mComputeDirtyBits);
3762}
3763
3764angle::Result Context::syncState(const State::DirtyBits &bitMask,
3765 const State::DirtyObjects &objectMask,
3766 Command command)
3767{
3768 ANGLE_TRY(syncDirtyObjects(objectMask, command));
3769 ANGLE_TRY(syncDirtyBits(bitMask));
3770 return angle::Result::Continue;
3771}
3772
3773void Context::blitFramebuffer(GLint srcX0,
3774 GLint srcY0,
3775 GLint srcX1,
3776 GLint srcY1,
3777 GLint dstX0,
3778 GLint dstY0,
3779 GLint dstX1,
3780 GLint dstY1,
3781 GLbitfield mask,
3782 GLenum filter)
3783{
3784 if (mask == 0)
3785 {
3786 // ES3.0 spec, section 4.3.2 specifies that a mask of zero is valid and no
3787 // buffers are copied.
3788 return;
3789 }
3790
3791 Framebuffer *drawFramebuffer = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3792 ASSERT(drawFramebuffer);
3793
3794 // Note that blitting is called against draw framebuffer.
3795 // See the code in gl::Context::blitFramebuffer.
3796 if ((mask & GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT) && !drawFramebuffer->hasEnabledDrawBuffer())
3797 {
3798 mask &= ~GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
3799 }
3800
3801 if ((mask & GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT) &&
3802 drawFramebuffer->getState().getStencilAttachment() == nullptr)
3803 {
3804 mask &= ~GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
3805 }
3806
3807 if ((mask & GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT) && drawFramebuffer->getState().getDepthAttachment() == nullptr)
3808 {
3809 mask &= ~GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT;
3810 }
3811
3812 // Early out if none of the specified attachments exist or are enabled.
3813 if (mask == 0)
3814 {
3815 ANGLE_PERF_WARNING(mState.getDebug(), GL_DEBUG_SEVERITY_LOW,
3816 "BlitFramebuffer called for non-existing buffers");
3817 return;
3818 }
3819
3820 Rectangle srcArea(srcX0, srcY0, srcX1 - srcX0, srcY1 - srcY0);
3821 Rectangle dstArea(dstX0, dstY0, dstX1 - dstX0, dstY1 - dstY0);
3822
3823 if (dstArea.width == 0 || dstArea.height == 0)
3824 {
3825 return;
3826 }
3827
3828 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncStateForBlit());
3829
3830 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(drawFramebuffer->blit(this, srcArea, dstArea, mask, filter));
3831}
3832
3833void Context::clear(GLbitfield mask)
3834{
3835 if (mState.isRasterizerDiscardEnabled())
3836 {
3837 return;
3838 }
3839
3840 // Noop empty scissors.
3841 if (IsEmptyScissor(mState))
3842 {
3843 return;
3844 }
3845
3846 // Remove clear bits that are ineffective. An effective clear changes at least one fragment. If
3847 // color/depth/stencil masks make the clear ineffective we skip it altogether.
3848
3849 // If all color channels in all draw buffers are masked, don't attempt to clear color.
3850 if (mState.allActiveDrawBufferChannelsMasked())
3851 {
3852 mask &= ~GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
3853 }
3854
3855 // If depth write is disabled, don't attempt to clear depth.
3856 if (mState.getDrawFramebuffer()->getDepthAttachment() == nullptr ||
3857 !mState.getDepthStencilState().depthMask)
3858 {
3859 mask &= ~GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT;
3860 }
3861
3862 // If all stencil bits are masked, don't attempt to clear stencil.
3863 if (mState.getDrawFramebuffer()->getStencilAttachment() == nullptr ||
3864 mState.getDepthStencilState().stencilWritemask == 0)
3865 {
3866 mask &= ~GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
3867 }
3868
3869 if (mask == 0)
3870 {
3871 ANGLE_PERF_WARNING(mState.getDebug(), GL_DEBUG_SEVERITY_LOW,
3872 "Clear called for non-existing buffers");
3873 return;
3874 }
3875
3876 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForClear(mask));
3877 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.getDrawFramebuffer()->clear(this, mask));
3878}
3879
3880bool Context::isClearBufferMaskedOut(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer) const
3881{
3882 switch (buffer)
3883 {
3884 case GL_COLOR:
3885 return IsColorMaskedOut(mState.getBlendStateExt(), drawbuffer);
3886 case GL_DEPTH:
3887 return mState.getDepthStencilState().isDepthMaskedOut();
3888 case GL_STENCIL:
3889 return mState.getDepthStencilState().isStencilMaskedOut();
3890 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL:
3891 return mState.getDepthStencilState().isDepthMaskedOut() &&
3892 mState.getDepthStencilState().isStencilMaskedOut();
3893 default:
3894 UNREACHABLE();
3895 return true;
3896 }
3897}
3898
3899bool Context::noopClearBuffer(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer) const
3900{
3901 Framebuffer *framebufferObject = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3902
3903 return !IsClearBufferEnabled(framebufferObject->getState(), buffer, drawbuffer) ||
3904 mState.isRasterizerDiscardEnabled() || isClearBufferMaskedOut(buffer, drawbuffer) ||
3905 IsEmptyScissor(mState);
3906}
3907
3908void Context::clearBufferfv(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer, const GLfloat *values)
3909{
3910 if (noopClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer))
3911 {
3912 return;
3913 }
3914
3915 Framebuffer *framebufferObject = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3916 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment = nullptr;
3917 if (buffer == GL_DEPTH)
3918 {
3919 attachment = framebufferObject->getDepthAttachment();
3920 }
3921 else if (buffer == GL_COLOR &&
3922 static_cast<size_t>(drawbuffer) < framebufferObject->getNumColorAttachments())
3923 {
3924 attachment = framebufferObject->getColorAttachment(drawbuffer);
3925 }
3926 // It's not an error to try to clear a non-existent buffer, but it's a no-op. We early out so
3927 // that the backend doesn't need to take this case into account.
3928 if (!attachment)
3929 {
3930 return;
3931 }
3932 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer));
3933 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebufferObject->clearBufferfv(this, buffer, drawbuffer, values));
3934}
3935
3936void Context::clearBufferuiv(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer, const GLuint *values)
3937{
3938 if (noopClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer))
3939 {
3940 return;
3941 }
3942
3943 Framebuffer *framebufferObject = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3944 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment = nullptr;
3945 if (buffer == GL_COLOR &&
3946 static_cast<size_t>(drawbuffer) < framebufferObject->getNumColorAttachments())
3947 {
3948 attachment = framebufferObject->getColorAttachment(drawbuffer);
3949 }
3950 // It's not an error to try to clear a non-existent buffer, but it's a no-op. We early out so
3951 // that the backend doesn't need to take this case into account.
3952 if (!attachment)
3953 {
3954 return;
3955 }
3956 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer));
3957 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebufferObject->clearBufferuiv(this, buffer, drawbuffer, values));
3958}
3959
3960void Context::clearBufferiv(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer, const GLint *values)
3961{
3962 if (noopClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer))
3963 {
3964 return;
3965 }
3966
3967 Framebuffer *framebufferObject = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3968 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment = nullptr;
3969 if (buffer == GL_STENCIL)
3970 {
3971 attachment = framebufferObject->getStencilAttachment();
3972 }
3973 else if (buffer == GL_COLOR &&
3974 static_cast<size_t>(drawbuffer) < framebufferObject->getNumColorAttachments())
3975 {
3976 attachment = framebufferObject->getColorAttachment(drawbuffer);
3977 }
3978 // It's not an error to try to clear a non-existent buffer, but it's a no-op. We early out so
3979 // that the backend doesn't need to take this case into account.
3980 if (!attachment)
3981 {
3982 return;
3983 }
3984 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer));
3985 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebufferObject->clearBufferiv(this, buffer, drawbuffer, values));
3986}
3987
3988void Context::clearBufferfi(GLenum buffer, GLint drawbuffer, GLfloat depth, GLint stencil)
3989{
3990 if (noopClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer))
3991 {
3992 return;
3993 }
3994
3995 Framebuffer *framebufferObject = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
3996 ASSERT(framebufferObject);
3997
3998 // If a buffer is not present, the clear has no effect
3999 if (framebufferObject->getDepthAttachment() == nullptr &&
4000 framebufferObject->getStencilAttachment() == nullptr)
4001 {
4002 return;
4003 }
4004
4005 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForClearBuffer(buffer, drawbuffer));
4006 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebufferObject->clearBufferfi(this, buffer, drawbuffer, depth, stencil));
4007}

4029 Buffer *packBuffer = mState.getTargetBuffer(gl::BufferBinding::PixelPack);

4031}

4134
4135void Context::copyImageSubData(GLuint srcName,
4136 GLenum srcTarget,
4137 GLint srcLevel,
4138 GLint srcX,
4139 GLint srcY,
4140 GLint srcZ,
4141 GLuint dstName,
4142 GLenum dstTarget,
4143 GLint dstLevel,
4144 GLint dstX,
4145 GLint dstY,
4146 GLint dstZ,
4147 GLsizei srcWidth,
4148 GLsizei srcHeight,
4149 GLsizei srcDepth)
4150{
4151 // if copy region is zero, the copy is a successful no-op
4152 if ((srcWidth == 0) || (srcHeight == 0) || (srcDepth == 0))
4153 {
4154 return;
4155 }
4156
4157 if (srcTarget == GL_RENDERBUFFER)
4158 {
4159 // Source target is a Renderbuffer
4160 Renderbuffer *readBuffer = getRenderbuffer(FromGL<RenderbufferID>(srcName));
4161 if (dstTarget == GL_RENDERBUFFER)
4162 {
4163 // Destination target is a Renderbuffer
4164 Renderbuffer *writeBuffer = getRenderbuffer(FromGL<RenderbufferID>(dstName));
4165
4166 // Copy Renderbuffer to Renderbuffer
4167 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(writeBuffer->copyRenderbufferSubData(
4168 this, readBuffer, srcLevel, srcX, srcY, srcZ, dstLevel, dstX, dstY, dstZ, srcWidth,
4169 srcHeight, srcDepth));
4170 }
4171 else
4172 {
4173 // Destination target is a Texture
4174 ASSERT(dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D || dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY ||
4175 dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_3D || dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP);
4176
4177 Texture *writeTexture = getTexture(FromGL<TextureID>(dstName));
4178 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncTextureForCopy(writeTexture));
4179
4180 // Copy Renderbuffer to Texture
4181 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(writeTexture->copyRenderbufferSubData(
4182 this, readBuffer, srcLevel, srcX, srcY, srcZ, dstLevel, dstX, dstY, dstZ, srcWidth,
4183 srcHeight, srcDepth));
4184 }
4185 }
4186 else
4187 {
4188 // Source target is a Texture
4189 ASSERT(srcTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D || srcTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY ||
4190 srcTarget == GL_TEXTURE_3D || srcTarget == GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP);
4191
4192 Texture *readTexture = getTexture(FromGL<TextureID>(srcName));
4193 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncTextureForCopy(readTexture));
4194
4195 if (dstTarget == GL_RENDERBUFFER)
4196 {
4197 // Destination target is a Renderbuffer
4198 Renderbuffer *writeBuffer = getRenderbuffer(FromGL<RenderbufferID>(dstName));
4199
4200 // Copy Texture to Renderbuffer
4201 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(writeBuffer->copyTextureSubData(this, readTexture, srcLevel, srcX,
4202 srcY, srcZ, dstLevel, dstX, dstY,
4203 dstZ, srcWidth, srcHeight, srcDepth));
4204 }
4205 else
4206 {
4207 // Destination target is a Texture
4208 ASSERT(dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D || dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY ||
4209 dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_3D || dstTarget == GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP);
4210
4211 Texture *writeTexture = getTexture(FromGL<TextureID>(dstName));
4212 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncTextureForCopy(writeTexture));
4213
4214 // Copy Texture to Texture
4215 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(writeTexture->copyTextureSubData(
4216 this, readTexture, srcLevel, srcX, srcY, srcZ, dstLevel, dstX, dstY, dstZ, srcWidth,
4217 srcHeight, srcDepth));
4218 }
4219 }
4220}
4221
4222void Context::framebufferTexture2D(GLenum target,
4223 GLenum attachment,
4224 TextureTarget textarget,
4225 TextureID texture,
4226 GLint level)
4227{
4228 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4229 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4230
4231 if (texture.value != 0)
4232 {
4233 Texture *textureObj = getTexture(texture);
4234 ImageIndex index = ImageIndex::MakeFromTarget(textarget, level, 1);
4235 framebuffer->setAttachment(this, GL_TEXTURE, attachment, index, textureObj);
4236 }
4237 else
4238 {
4239 framebuffer->resetAttachment(this, attachment);
4240 }
4241
4242 mState.setObjectDirty(target);
4243}

4269void Context::framebufferRenderbuffer(GLenum target,
4270 GLenum attachment,
4271 GLenum renderbuffertarget,
4272 RenderbufferID renderbuffer)
4273{
4274 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4275 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4276
4277 if (renderbuffer.value != 0)
4278 {
4279 Renderbuffer *renderbufferObject = getRenderbuffer(renderbuffer);
4280 GLsizei rbSamples = renderbufferObject->getState().getSamples();
4281
4282 framebuffer->setAttachmentMultisample(this, GL_RENDERBUFFER, attachment, gl::ImageIndex(),
4283 renderbufferObject, rbSamples);
4284 }
4285 else
4286 {
4287 framebuffer->resetAttachment(this, attachment);
4288 }
4289
4290 mState.setObjectDirty(target);
4291}

4316void Context::framebufferTextureMultiview(GLenum target,
4317 GLenum attachment,
4318 TextureID texture,
4319 GLint level,
4320 GLint baseViewIndex,
4321 GLsizei numViews)
4322{
4323 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4324 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4325
4326 if (texture.value != 0)
4327 {
4328 Texture *textureObj = getTexture(texture);
4329
4330 ImageIndex index;
4331 if (textureObj->getType() == TextureType::_2DArray)
4332 {
4333 index = ImageIndex::Make2DArrayRange(level, baseViewIndex, numViews);
4334 }
4335 else
4336 {
4337 ASSERT(textureObj->getType() == TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray);
4338 ASSERT(level == 0);
4339 index = ImageIndex::Make2DMultisampleArrayRange(baseViewIndex, numViews);
4340 }
4341 framebuffer->setAttachmentMultiview(this, GL_TEXTURE, attachment, index, textureObj,
4342 numViews, baseViewIndex);
4343 }
4344 else
4345 {
4346 framebuffer->resetAttachment(this, attachment);
4347 }
4348
4349 mState.setObjectDirty(target);
4350}

4352void Context::framebufferTexture(GLenum target, GLenum attachment, TextureID texture, GLint level)
4353{
4354 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4355 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4356
4357 if (texture.value != 0)
4358 {
4359 Texture *textureObj = getTexture(texture);
4360
4361 ImageIndex index = ImageIndex::MakeFromType(
4362 textureObj->getType(), level, ImageIndex::kEntireLevel, ImageIndex::kEntireLevel);
4363 framebuffer->setAttachment(this, GL_TEXTURE, attachment, index, textureObj);
4364 }
4365 else

4367 framebuffer->resetAttachment(this, attachment);
4368 }
4369
4370 mState.setObjectDirty(target);
4371}

4388
4389void Context::discardFramebuffer(GLenum target, GLsizei numAttachments, const GLenum *attachments)
4390{
4391 // Only sync the FBO
4392 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.syncDirtyObject(this, target));
4393
4394 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4395 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4396
4397 // The specification isn't clear what should be done when the framebuffer isn't complete.
4398 // We leave it up to the framebuffer implementation to decide what to do.
4399 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebuffer->discard(this, numAttachments, attachments));
4400}
4401
4402void Context::invalidateFramebuffer(GLenum target,
4403 GLsizei numAttachments,
4404 const GLenum *attachments)
4405{
4406 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4407 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4408
4409 // No-op incomplete FBOs.
4410 if (!framebuffer->isComplete(this))
4411 {
4412 return;
4413 }
4414
4415 // Only sync the FBO
4416 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.syncDirtyObject(this, target));
4417 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebuffer->invalidate(this, numAttachments, attachments));
4418}
4419
4420void Context::invalidateSubFramebuffer(GLenum target,
4421 GLsizei numAttachments,
4422 const GLenum *attachments,
4423 GLint x,
4424 GLint y,
4425 GLsizei width,
4426 GLsizei height)
4427{
4428 Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getTargetFramebuffer(target);
4429 ASSERT(framebuffer);
4430
4431 if (!framebuffer->isComplete(this))
4432 {
4433 return;
4434 }
4435
4436 Rectangle area(x, y, width, height);
4437 // Only sync the FBO
4438 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.syncDirtyObject(this, target));
4439 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebuffer->invalidateSub(this, numAttachments, attachments, area));
4440}

4702void Context::compressedTexSubImage3D(TextureTarget target,

4708 GLsizei height,
4709 GLsizei depth,
4710 GLenum format,

4718 }

4722 Box area(xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth);
4723 Texture *texture = getTextureByTarget(target);
4724 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(texture->setCompressedSubImage(this, mState.getUnpackState(), target, level,
4725 area, format, imageSize,
4726 static_cast<const uint8_t *>(data)));
4727}

4751
4752void Context::copyTexture(TextureID sourceId,
4753 GLint sourceLevel,
4754 TextureTarget destTarget,
4755 TextureID destId,
4756 GLint destLevel,
4757 GLint internalFormat,
4758 GLenum destType,
4759 GLboolean unpackFlipY,
4760 GLboolean unpackPremultiplyAlpha,
4761 GLboolean unpackUnmultiplyAlpha)
4762{
4763 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncStateForTexImage());
4764
4765 gl::Texture *sourceTexture = getTexture(sourceId);
4766 gl::Texture *destTexture = getTexture(destId);
4767 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(
4768 destTexture->copyTexture(this, destTarget, destLevel, internalFormat, destType, sourceLevel,
4769 ConvertToBool(unpackFlipY), ConvertToBool(unpackPremultiplyAlpha),
4770 ConvertToBool(unpackUnmultiplyAlpha), sourceTexture));
4771}
4772
4773void Context::copySubTexture(TextureID sourceId,
4774 GLint sourceLevel,
4775 TextureTarget destTarget,
4776 TextureID destId,
4777 GLint destLevel,
4778 GLint xoffset,
4779 GLint yoffset,
4780 GLint x,
4781 GLint y,
4782 GLsizei width,
4783 GLsizei height,
4784 GLboolean unpackFlipY,
4785 GLboolean unpackPremultiplyAlpha,
4786 GLboolean unpackUnmultiplyAlpha)
4787{
4788 // Zero sized copies are valid but no-ops
4789 if (width == 0 || height == 0)
4790 {
4791 return;
4792 }
4793
4794 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncStateForTexImage());
4795
4796 gl::Texture *sourceTexture = getTexture(sourceId);
4797 gl::Texture *destTexture = getTexture(destId);
4798 Offset offset(xoffset, yoffset, 0);
4799 Box box(x, y, 0, width, height, 1);
4800 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(destTexture->copySubTexture(
4801 this, destTarget, destLevel, offset, sourceLevel, box, ConvertToBool(unpackFlipY),
4802 ConvertToBool(unpackPremultiplyAlpha), ConvertToBool(unpackUnmultiplyAlpha),
4803 sourceTexture));
4804}

4888
4889void *Context::mapBuffer(BufferBinding target, GLenum access)
4890{
4891 Buffer *buffer = mState.getTargetBuffer(target);
4892 ASSERT(buffer);
4893
4894 if (buffer->map(this, access) == angle::Result::Stop)
4895 {
4896 return nullptr;
4897 }
4898
4899 return buffer->getMapPointer();
4900}
4901
4902GLboolean Context::unmapBuffer(BufferBinding target)
4903{
4904 Buffer *buffer = mState.getTargetBuffer(target);
4905 ASSERT(buffer);
4906
4907 GLboolean result;
4908 if (buffer->unmap(this, &result) == angle::Result::Stop)
4909 {
4910 return GL_FALSE;
4911 }
4912
4913 return result;
4914}
4915
4916void *Context::mapBufferRange(BufferBinding target,
4917 GLintptr offset,
4918 GLsizeiptr length,
4919 GLbitfield access)
4920{
4921 Buffer *buffer = mState.getTargetBuffer(target);
4922 ASSERT(buffer);
4923
4924 if (buffer->mapRange(this, offset, length, access) == angle::Result::Stop)
4925 {
4926 return nullptr;
4927 }
4928
4929 return buffer->getMapPointer();
4930}

4958
4959angle::Result Context::syncTextureForCopy(Texture *texture)
4960{
4961 ASSERT(texture);
4962 // Sync texture not active but scheduled for a copy
4963 if (texture->hasAnyDirtyBit())
4964 {
4965 return texture->syncState(this, Command::Other);
4966 }
4967
4968 return angle::Result::Continue;
4969}

4980}

5140
5141void Context::hint(GLenum target, GLenum mode)
5142{
5143 switch (target)
5144 {
5145 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT:
5146 mState.setGenerateMipmapHint(mode);
5147 break;
5148
5149 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES:
5150 mState.setFragmentShaderDerivativeHint(mode);
5151 break;
5152
5153 case GL_PERSPECTIVE_CORRECTION_HINT:
5154 case GL_POINT_SMOOTH_HINT:
5155 case GL_LINE_SMOOTH_HINT:
5156 case GL_FOG_HINT:
5157 mState.gles1().setHint(target, mode);
5158 break;
5159 case GL_TEXTURE_FILTERING_HINT_CHROMIUM:
5160 mState.setTextureFilteringHint(mode);
5161 break;
5162 default:
5163 UNREACHABLE();
5164 return;
5165 }
5166}

5172
5173void Context::pixelStorei(GLenum pname, GLint param)
5174{
5175 switch (pname)
5176 {
5177 case GL_UNPACK_ALIGNMENT:
5178 mState.setUnpackAlignment(param);
5179 break;
5180
5181 case GL_PACK_ALIGNMENT:
5182 mState.setPackAlignment(param);
5183 break;
5184
5185 case GL_PACK_REVERSE_ROW_ORDER_ANGLE:
5186 mState.setPackReverseRowOrder(param != 0);
5187 break;
5188
5189 case GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH:
5190 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().unpackSubimage);
5191 mState.setUnpackRowLength(param);
5192 break;
5193
5194 case GL_UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT:
5195 ASSERT(getClientMajorVersion() >= 3);
5196 mState.setUnpackImageHeight(param);
5197 break;
5198
5199 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES:
5200 ASSERT(getClientMajorVersion() >= 3);
5201 mState.setUnpackSkipImages(param);
5202 break;
5203
5204 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS:
5205 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().unpackSubimage);
5206 mState.setUnpackSkipRows(param);
5207 break;
5208
5209 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
5210 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().unpackSubimage);
5211 mState.setUnpackSkipPixels(param);
5212 break;
5213
5214 case GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH:
5215 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().packSubimage);
5216 mState.setPackRowLength(param);
5217 break;
5218
5219 case GL_PACK_SKIP_ROWS:
5220 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().packSubimage);
5221 mState.setPackSkipRows(param);
5222 break;
5223
5224 case GL_PACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
5225 ASSERT((getClientMajorVersion() >= 3) || getExtensions().packSubimage);
5226 mState.setPackSkipPixels(param);
5227 break;
5228
5229 default:
5230 UNREACHABLE();
5231 return;
5232 }
5233}

5255void Context::stencilFuncSeparate(GLenum face, GLenum func, GLint ref, GLuint mask)
5256{
5257 GLint clampedRef = gl::clamp(ref, 0, std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max());
5258 if (face == GL_FRONT || face == GL_FRONT_AND_BACK)
5259 {
5260 mState.setStencilParams(func, clampedRef, mask);
5261 }
5262
5263 if (face == GL_BACK || face == GL_FRONT_AND_BACK)
5264 {
5265 mState.setStencilBackParams(func, clampedRef, mask);
5266 }
5267
5268 mStateCache.onStencilStateChange(this);
5269}
5270
5271void Context::stencilMaskSeparate(GLenum face, GLuint mask)
5272{
5273 if (face == GL_FRONT || face == GL_FRONT_AND_BACK)
5274 {
5275 mState.setStencilWritemask(mask);
5276 }
5277
5278 if (face == GL_BACK || face == GL_FRONT_AND_BACK)
5279 {
5280 mState.setStencilBackWritemask(mask);
5281 }
5282
5283 mStateCache.onStencilStateChange(this);
5284}

5440void Context::getVertexAttribivImpl(GLuint index, GLenum pname, GLint *params) const
5441{
5442 const VertexAttribCurrentValueData &currentValues =
5443 getState().getVertexAttribCurrentValue(index);

5777void Context::getMultisamplefv(GLenum pname, GLuint index, GLfloat *val)
5778{
5779 // According to spec 3.1 Table 20.49: Framebuffer Dependent Values,
5780 // the sample position should be queried by DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER.
5781 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mState.syncDirtyObject(this, GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER));
5782 const Framebuffer *framebuffer = mState.getDrawFramebuffer();
5783
5784 switch (pname)
5785 {
5786 case GL_SAMPLE_POSITION:
5787 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(framebuffer->getSamplePosition(this, index, val));
5788 break;
5789 default:
5790 UNREACHABLE();
5791 }
5792}

5850void Context::framebufferTexture2DMultisample(GLenum target,
5851 GLenum attachment,

5853 TextureID texture,

5861 {
5862 Texture *textureObj = getTexture(texture);

5864 framebuffer->setAttachmentMultisample(this, GL_TEXTURE, attachment, index, textureObj,
5865 samples);
5866 }
5867 else
5868 {
5869 framebuffer->resetAttachment(this, attachment);
5870 }
5871
5872 mState.setObjectDirty(target);
5873}

5916}

5940
5941void Context::dispatchCompute(GLuint numGroupsX, GLuint numGroupsY, GLuint numGroupsZ)
5942{
5943 if (numGroupsX == 0u || numGroupsY == 0u || numGroupsZ == 0u)
5944 {
5945 return;
5946 }
5947
5948 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDispatch());
5949
5950 angle::Result result =
5951 mImplementation->dispatchCompute(this, numGroupsX, numGroupsY, numGroupsZ);
5952
5953 // This must be called before convertPpoToComputeOrDraw() so it uses the PPO's compute values
5954 // before convertPpoToComputeOrDraw() reverts the PPO back to graphics.
5955 MarkShaderStorageUsage(this);
5956
5957 // We always assume PPOs are used for draws, until they aren't. If we just executed a dispatch
5958 // with a PPO, we need to convert it back to a "draw"-type.
5959 // We don't re-link the PPO again, since it's possible for that link to generate validation
5960 // errors due to bad VS/FS, and we want to catch those errors during validation of the draw
5961 // command: 11.1.3.11 Validation It is not always possible to determine at link time if a
5962 // program object can execute successfully, given that LinkProgram can not know the state of the
5963 // remainder of the pipeline. Therefore validation is done when the first rendering command
5964 // which triggers shader invocations is issued, to determine if the set of active program
5965 // objects can be executed.
5966 convertPpoToComputeOrDraw(false);
5967
5968 if (ANGLE_UNLIKELY(IsError(result)))
5969 {
5970 return;
5971 }
5972}
5973
5974void Context::convertPpoToComputeOrDraw(bool isCompute)
5975{
5976 Program *program = mState.getProgram();
5977 ProgramPipeline *pipeline = mState.getProgramPipeline();
5978 if (!program && pipeline)
5979 {
5980 pipeline->getExecutable().setIsCompute(isCompute);
5981 pipeline->resetIsLinked();
5982
5983 // The PPO's isCompute() has changed, so its ProgramExecutable will produce different
5984 // results for things like getShaderStorageBlocks() or getImageBindings().
5985 mState.mDirtyBits.set(State::DirtyBitType::DIRTY_BIT_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE);
5986 mStateCache.onProgramExecutableChange(this);
5987 }
5988}
5989
5990void Context::dispatchComputeIndirect(GLintptr indirect)
5991{
5992 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDispatch());
5993 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->dispatchComputeIndirect(this, indirect));
5994
5995 MarkShaderStorageUsage(this);
5996}

6073
6074void Context::drawArraysInstancedBaseInstance(PrimitiveMode mode,
6075 GLint first,
6076 GLsizei count,
6077 GLsizei instanceCount,
6078 GLuint baseInstance)
6079{
6080 if (noopDraw(mode, count))
6081 {
6082 return;
6083 }
6084
6085 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDraw(mode));
6086 Program *programObject = mState.getLinkedProgram(this);
6087
6088 const bool hasBaseInstance = programObject && programObject->hasBaseInstanceUniform();
6089 if (hasBaseInstance)
6090 {
6091 programObject->setBaseInstanceUniform(baseInstance);
6092 }
6093
6094 rx::ResetBaseVertexBaseInstance resetUniforms(programObject, false, hasBaseInstance);
6095
6096 // The input gl_InstanceID does not follow the baseinstance. gl_InstanceID always falls on
6097 // the half-open range [0, instancecount). No need to set other stuff. Except for Vulkan.
6098
6099 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->drawArraysInstancedBaseInstance(
6100 this, mode, first, count, instanceCount, baseInstance));
6101 MarkTransformFeedbackBufferUsage(this, count, 1);
6102}
6103
6104void Context::drawElementsInstancedBaseVertexBaseInstance(PrimitiveMode mode,
6105 GLsizei count,
6106 DrawElementsType type,
6107 const GLvoid *indices,
6108 GLsizei instanceCounts,
6109 GLint baseVertex,
6110 GLuint baseInstance)
6111{
6112 if (noopDraw(mode, count))
6113 {
6114 return;
6115 }
6116
6117 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDraw(mode));
6118 Program *programObject = mState.getLinkedProgram(this);
6119
6120 const bool hasBaseVertex = programObject && programObject->hasBaseVertexUniform();
6121 if (hasBaseVertex)
6122 {
6123 programObject->setBaseVertexUniform(baseVertex);
6124 }
6125
6126 const bool hasBaseInstance = programObject && programObject->hasBaseInstanceUniform();
6127 if (hasBaseInstance)
6128 {
6129 programObject->setBaseInstanceUniform(baseInstance);
6130 }
6131
6132 rx::ResetBaseVertexBaseInstance resetUniforms(programObject, hasBaseVertex, hasBaseInstance);
6133
6134 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->drawElementsInstancedBaseVertexBaseInstance(
6135 this, mode, count, type, indices, instanceCounts, baseVertex, baseInstance));
6136}
6137
6138void Context::multiDrawArraysInstancedBaseInstance(PrimitiveMode mode,
6139 const GLint *firsts,
6140 const GLsizei *counts,
6141 const GLsizei *instanceCounts,
6142 const GLuint *baseInstances,
6143 GLsizei drawcount)
6144{
6145 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(prepareForDraw(mode));
6146 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(mImplementation->multiDrawArraysInstancedBaseInstance(

6310void Context::getBooleanv(GLenum pname, GLboolean *params)
6311{
6312 GLenum nativeType;
6313 unsigned int numParams = 0;
6314 getQueryParameterInfo(pname, &nativeType, &numParams);
6315
6316 if (nativeType == GL_BOOL)
6317 {
6318 getBooleanvImpl(pname, params);
6319 }
6320 else
6321 {
6322 CastStateValues(this, nativeType, pname, numParams, params);
6323 }
6324}

6373void Context::getProgramiv(ShaderProgramID program, GLenum pname, GLint *params)
6374{
6375 // Don't resolve link if checking the link completion status.
6376 Program *programObject = getProgramNoResolveLink(program);
6377 if (!isContextLost() && pname != GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
6378 {
6379 programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
6380 }
6381 ASSERT(programObject);
6382 QueryProgramiv(this, programObject, pname, params);
6383}

6386 GLenum pname,

6392}

6397 if (!mContextLost)
6398 {
6399 programPipeline = getProgramPipeline(pipeline);
6400 }
6401 QueryProgramPipelineiv(this, programPipeline, pname, params);
6402}

6470
6471void Context::getShaderPrecisionFormat(GLenum shadertype,
6472 GLenum precisiontype,
6473 GLint *range,
6474 GLint *precision)
6475{
6476 // TODO(jmadill): Compute shaders.
6477
6478 switch (shadertype)
6479 {
6480 case GL_VERTEX_SHADER:
6481 switch (precisiontype)
6482 {
6483 case GL_LOW_FLOAT:
6484 mState.mCaps.vertexLowpFloat.get(range, precision);
6485 break;
6486 case GL_MEDIUM_FLOAT:
6487 mState.mCaps.vertexMediumpFloat.get(range, precision);
6488 break;
6489 case GL_HIGH_FLOAT:
6490 mState.mCaps.vertexHighpFloat.get(range, precision);
6491 break;
6492
6493 case GL_LOW_INT:
6494 mState.mCaps.vertexLowpInt.get(range, precision);
6495 break;
6496 case GL_MEDIUM_INT:
6497 mState.mCaps.vertexMediumpInt.get(range, precision);
6498 break;
6499 case GL_HIGH_INT:
6500 mState.mCaps.vertexHighpInt.get(range, precision);
6501 break;
6502
6503 default:
6504 UNREACHABLE();
6505 return;
6506 }
6507 break;
6508
6509 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
6510 switch (precisiontype)
6511 {
6512 case GL_LOW_FLOAT:
6513 mState.mCaps.fragmentLowpFloat.get(range, precision);
6514 break;
6515 case GL_MEDIUM_FLOAT:
6516 mState.mCaps.fragmentMediumpFloat.get(range, precision);
6517 break;
6518 case GL_HIGH_FLOAT:
6519 mState.mCaps.fragmentHighpFloat.get(range, precision);
6520 break;
6521
6522 case GL_LOW_INT:
6523 mState.mCaps.fragmentLowpInt.get(range, precision);
6524 break;
6525 case GL_MEDIUM_INT:
6526 mState.mCaps.fragmentMediumpInt.get(range, precision);
6527 break;
6528 case GL_HIGH_INT:
6529 mState.mCaps.fragmentHighpInt.get(range, precision);
6530 break;
6531
6532 default:
6533 UNREACHABLE();
6534 return;
6535 }
6536 break;
6537
6538 default:
6539 UNREACHABLE();
6540 return;
6541 }
6542}

6746Program *Context::getActiveLinkedProgram() const
6747{
6748 Program *program = mState.getLinkedProgram(this);
6749 if (!program)
6750 {
6751 ProgramPipeline *programPipelineObject = mState.getProgramPipeline();
6752 if (programPipelineObject)
6753 {
6754 program = programPipelineObject->getLinkedActiveShaderProgram(this);
6755 }
6756 }
6757
6758 return program;
6759}

6920
6921void Context::getProgramBinary(ShaderProgramID program,
6922 GLsizei bufSize,
6923 GLsizei *length,
6924 GLenum *binaryFormat,
6925 void *binary)
6926{
6927 Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
6928 ASSERT(programObject != nullptr);
6929
6930 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(programObject->saveBinary(this, binaryFormat, binary, bufSize, length));
6931}
6932
6933void Context::programBinary(ShaderProgramID program,
6934 GLenum binaryFormat,
6935 const void *binary,
6936 GLsizei length)
6937{
6938 Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
6939 ASSERT(programObject != nullptr);
6940
6941 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(programObject->loadBinary(this, binaryFormat, binary, length));
6942 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(onProgramLink(programObject));
6943}

6994
6995void Context::genQueries(GLsizei n, QueryID *ids)
6996{
6997 for (GLsizei i = 0; i < n; i++)
6998 {
6999 QueryID handle = QueryID{mQueryHandleAllocator.allocate()};
7000 mQueryMap.assign(handle, nullptr);
7001 ids[i] = handle;
7002 }
7003}
7004
7005void Context::deleteQueries(GLsizei n, const QueryID *ids)
7006{
7007 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
7008 {
7009 QueryID query = ids[i];
7010
7011 Query *queryObject = nullptr;
7012 if (mQueryMap.erase(query, &queryObject))
7013 {
7014 mQueryHandleAllocator.release(query.value);
7015 if (queryObject)
7016 {
7017 queryObject->release(this);
7018 }
7019 }
7020 }
7021}
7022
7023bool Context::isQueryGenerated(QueryID query) const
7024{
7025 return mQueryMap.contains(query);
7026}
7027
7028GLboolean Context::isQuery(QueryID id) const
7029{
7030 return ConvertToGLBoolean(getQuery(id) != nullptr);
7031}

7086
7087void Context::deleteVertexArrays(GLsizei n, const VertexArrayID *arrays)
7088{
7089 for (int arrayIndex = 0; arrayIndex < n; arrayIndex++)
7090 {
7091 VertexArrayID vertexArray = arrays[arrayIndex];
7092
7093 if (arrays[arrayIndex].value != 0)
7094 {
7095 VertexArray *vertexArrayObject = nullptr;
7096 if (mVertexArrayMap.erase(vertexArray, &vertexArrayObject))
7097 {
7098 if (vertexArrayObject != nullptr)
7099 {
7100 detachVertexArray(vertexArray);
7101 vertexArrayObject->onDestroy(this);
7102 }
7103
7104 mVertexArrayHandleAllocator.release(vertexArray.value);
7105 }
7106 }
7107 }
7108}
7109
7110void Context::genVertexArrays(GLsizei n, VertexArrayID *arrays)
7111{
7112 for (int arrayIndex = 0; arrayIndex < n; arrayIndex++)
7113 {
7114 VertexArrayID vertexArray = {mVertexArrayHandleAllocator.allocate()};
7115 mVertexArrayMap.assign(vertexArray, nullptr);
7116 arrays[arrayIndex] = vertexArray;
7117 }
7118}
7119
7120GLboolean Context::isVertexArray(VertexArrayID array) const
7121{
7122 if (array.value == 0)
7123 {
7124 return GL_FALSE;
7125 }
7126
7127 VertexArray *vao = getVertexArray(array);
7128 return ConvertToGLBoolean(vao != nullptr);
7129}
7130
7131void Context::endTransformFeedback()
7132{
7133 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
7134 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(transformFeedback->end(this));
7135 mStateCache.onActiveTransformFeedbackChange(this);
7136}

7139 GLsizei count,
7140 const GLchar *const *varyings,
7141 GLenum bufferMode)
7142{
7143 Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
7144 ASSERT(programObject);
7145 programObject->setTransformFeedbackVaryings(count, varyings, bufferMode);
7146}
7147
7148void Context::getTransformFeedbackVarying(ShaderProgramID program,
7149 GLuint index,
7150 GLsizei bufSize,
7151 GLsizei *length,
7152 GLsizei *size,
7153 GLenum *type,
7154 GLchar *name)
7155{
7156 Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
7157 ASSERT(programObject);
7158 programObject->getTransformFeedbackVarying(index, bufSize, length, size, type, name);
7159}
7160
7161void Context::deleteTransformFeedbacks(GLsizei n, const TransformFeedbackID *ids)
7162{
7163 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
7164 {
7165 TransformFeedbackID transformFeedback = ids[i];
7166 if (transformFeedback.value == 0)
7167 {
7168 continue;
7169 }
7170
7171 TransformFeedback *transformFeedbackObject = nullptr;
7172 if (mTransformFeedbackMap.erase(transformFeedback, &transformFeedbackObject))
7173 {
7174 if (transformFeedbackObject != nullptr)
7175 {
7176 detachTransformFeedback(transformFeedback);
7177 transformFeedbackObject->release(this);
7178 }
7179
7180 mTransformFeedbackHandleAllocator.release(transformFeedback.value);
7181 }
7182 }
7183}
7184
7185void Context::genTransformFeedbacks(GLsizei n, TransformFeedbackID *ids)
7186{
7187 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
7188 {
7189 TransformFeedbackID transformFeedback = {mTransformFeedbackHandleAllocator.allocate()};
7190 mTransformFeedbackMap.assign(transformFeedback, nullptr);
7191 ids[i] = transformFeedback;
7192 }
7193}
7194
7195GLboolean Context::isTransformFeedback(TransformFeedbackID id) const
7196{
7197 if (id.value == 0)
7198 {
7199 // The 3.0.4 spec [section 6.1.11] states that if ID is zero, IsTransformFeedback
7200 // returns FALSE
7201 return GL_FALSE;
7202 }
7203
7204 const TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = getTransformFeedback(id);
7205 return ConvertToGLBoolean(transformFeedback != nullptr);
7206}
7207
7208void Context::pauseTransformFeedback()
7209{
7210 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
7211 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(transformFeedback->pause(this));
7212 mStateCache.onActiveTransformFeedbackChange(this);
7213}
7214
7215void Context::resumeTransformFeedback()
7216{
7217 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
7218 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(transformFeedback->resume(this));
7219 mStateCache.onActiveTransformFeedbackChange(this);
7220}

7242
7243void Context::getUniformIndices(ShaderProgramID program,
7244 GLsizei uniformCount,
7245 const GLchar *const *uniformNames,
7246 GLuint *uniformIndices)
7247{
7248 const Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
7249 if (!programObject->isLinked())
7250 {
7251 for (int uniformId = 0; uniformId < uniformCount; uniformId++)
7252 {
7253 uniformIndices[uniformId] = GL_INVALID_INDEX;
7254 }
7255 }
7256 else
7257 {
7258 for (int uniformId = 0; uniformId < uniformCount; uniformId++)
7259 {
7260 uniformIndices[uniformId] = programObject->getUniformIndex(uniformNames[uniformId]);
7261 }
7262 }
7263}
7264
7265void Context::getActiveUniformsiv(ShaderProgramID program,
7266 GLsizei uniformCount,
7267 const GLuint *uniformIndices,
7268 GLenum pname,
7269 GLint *params)
7270{
7271 const Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
7272 for (int uniformId = 0; uniformId < uniformCount; uniformId++)
7273 {
7274 const GLuint index = uniformIndices[uniformId];
7275 params[uniformId] = GetUniformResourceProperty(programObject, index, pname);
7276 }
7277}

7313
7314void Context::uniformBlockBinding(ShaderProgramID program,
7315 GLuint uniformBlockIndex,
7316 GLuint uniformBlockBinding)
7317{
7318 Program *programObject = getProgramResolveLink(program);
7319 programObject->bindUniformBlock(uniformBlockIndex, uniformBlockBinding);
7320
7321 // Note: If the Program is shared between Contexts we would be better using Observer/Subject.
7322 if (programObject->isInUse())
7323 {
7324 mState.setObjectDirty(GL_PROGRAM);
7325 mStateCache.onUniformBufferStateChange(this);
7326 }
7327}
7328
7329GLsync Context::fenceSync(GLenum condition, GLbitfield flags)
7330{
7331 GLuint handle = mState.mSyncManager->createSync(mImplementation.get());
7332 GLsync syncHandle = reinterpret_cast<GLsync>(static_cast<uintptr_t>(handle));
7333
7334 Sync *syncObject = getSync(syncHandle);
7335 if (syncObject->set(this, condition, flags) == angle::Result::Stop)
7336 {
7337 deleteSync(syncHandle);
7338 return nullptr;
7339 }
7340
7341 return syncHandle;
7342}
7343
7344GLboolean Context::isSync(GLsync sync) const
7345{
7346 return (getSync(sync) != nullptr);
7347}
7348
7349GLenum Context::clientWaitSync(GLsync sync, GLbitfield flags, GLuint64 timeout)
7350{
7351 Sync *syncObject = getSync(sync);
7352
7353 GLenum result = GL_WAIT_FAILED;
7354 if (syncObject->clientWait(this, flags, timeout, &result) == angle::Result::Stop)
7355 {
7356 return GL_WAIT_FAILED;
7357 }
7358 return result;
7359}
7360
7361void Context::waitSync(GLsync sync, GLbitfield flags, GLuint64 timeout)
7362{
7363 Sync *syncObject = getSync(sync);
7364 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(syncObject->serverWait(this, flags, timeout));
7365}
7366
7367void Context::getInteger64v(GLenum pname, GLint64 *params)
7368{
7369 GLenum nativeType = GL_NONE;
7370 unsigned int numParams = 0;
7371 getQueryParameterInfo(pname, &nativeType, &numParams);
7372
7373 if (nativeType == GL_INT_64_ANGLEX)
7374 {
7375 getInteger64vImpl(pname, params);
7376 }
7377 else
7378 {
7379 CastStateValues(this, nativeType, pname, numParams, params);
7380 }
7381}
7382
7383void Context::getInteger64vRobust(GLenum pname, GLsizei bufSize, GLsizei *length, GLint64 *data)
7384{
7385 getInteger64v(pname, data);
7386}

7411void Context::deleteSamplers(GLsizei count, const SamplerID *samplers)
7412{
7413 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
7414 {
7415 SamplerID sampler = samplers[i];
7416
7417 if (mState.mSamplerManager->getSampler(sampler))
7418 {
7419 detachSampler(sampler);
7420 }
7421
7422 mState.mSamplerManager->deleteObject(this, sampler);
7423 }

7681{

7799GLboolean Context::isProgramPipeline(ProgramPipelineID pipeline) const
7800{
7801 if (pipeline.value == 0)
7802 {
7803 return GL_FALSE;
7804 }
7805
7806 if (getProgramPipeline(pipeline))
7807 {
7808 return GL_TRUE;
7809 }
7810
7811 return GL_FALSE;
7812}
7813
7814void Context::finishFenceNV(FenceNVID fence)
7815{
7816 FenceNV *fenceObject = getFenceNV(fence);
7817
7818 ASSERT(fenceObject && fenceObject->isSet());
7819 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(fenceObject->finish(this));
7820}
7821
7822void Context::getFenceivNV(FenceNVID fence, GLenum pname, GLint *params)
7823{
7824 FenceNV *fenceObject = getFenceNV(fence);
7825
7826 ASSERT(fenceObject && fenceObject->isSet());
7827
7828 switch (pname)
7829 {
7830 case GL_FENCE_STATUS_NV:
7831 {
7832 // GL_NV_fence spec:
7833 // Once the status of a fence has been finished (via FinishFenceNV) or tested and
7834 // the returned status is TRUE (via either TestFenceNV or GetFenceivNV querying the
7835 // FENCE_STATUS_NV), the status remains TRUE until the next SetFenceNV of the fence.
7836 GLboolean status = GL_TRUE;
7837 if (fenceObject->getStatus() != GL_TRUE)
7838 {
7839 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(fenceObject->test(this, &status));
7840 }
7841 *params = status;
7842 break;
7843 }
7844
7845 case GL_FENCE_CONDITION_NV:
7846 {
7847 *params = static_cast<GLint>(fenceObject->getCondition());
7848 break;
7849 }
7850
7851 default:
7852 UNREACHABLE();
7853 }
7854}

7914
7915GLboolean Context::isFenceNV(FenceNVID fence) const
7916{
7917 FenceNV *fenceObject = getFenceNV(fence);
7918
7919 if (fenceObject == nullptr)
7920 {
7921 return GL_FALSE;
7922 }
7923
7924 // GL_NV_fence spec:
7925 // A name returned by GenFencesNV, but not yet set via SetFenceNV, is not the name of an
7926 // existing fence.
7927 return fenceObject->isSet();
7928}

7941
7942void Context::setFenceNV(FenceNVID fence, GLenum condition)
7943{
7944 ASSERT(condition == GL_ALL_COMPLETED_NV);
7945
7946 FenceNV *fenceObject = getFenceNV(fence);
7947 ASSERT(fenceObject != nullptr);
7948 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(fenceObject->set(this, condition));
7949}
7950
7951GLboolean Context::testFenceNV(FenceNVID fence)
7952{
7953 FenceNV *fenceObject = getFenceNV(fence);
7954
7955 ASSERT(fenceObject != nullptr);
7956 ASSERT(fenceObject->isSet() == GL_TRUE);
7957
7958 GLboolean result = GL_TRUE;
7959 if (fenceObject->test(this, &result) == angle::Result::Stop)
7960 {
7961 return GL_TRUE;
7962 }
7963
7964 return result;
7965}

8177
8178void Context::waitSemaphore(SemaphoreID semaphoreHandle,
8179 GLuint numBufferBarriers,
8180 const BufferID *buffers,
8181 GLuint numTextureBarriers,
8182 const TextureID *textures,
8183 const GLenum *srcLayouts)
8184{
8185 Semaphore *semaphore = getSemaphore(semaphoreHandle);
8186 ASSERT(semaphore);
8187
8188 BufferBarrierVector bufferBarriers(numBufferBarriers);
8189 for (GLuint bufferBarrierIdx = 0; bufferBarrierIdx < numBufferBarriers; bufferBarrierIdx++)
8190 {
8191 bufferBarriers[bufferBarrierIdx] = getBuffer(buffers[bufferBarrierIdx]);
8192 }
8193
8194 TextureBarrierVector textureBarriers(numTextureBarriers);
8195 for (GLuint textureBarrierIdx = 0; textureBarrierIdx < numTextureBarriers; textureBarrierIdx++)
8196 {
8197 textureBarriers[textureBarrierIdx].texture = getTexture(textures[textureBarrierIdx]);
8198 textureBarriers[textureBarrierIdx].layout = srcLayouts[textureBarrierIdx];
8199 }
8200
8201 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(semaphore->wait(this, bufferBarriers, textureBarriers));
8202}
8203
8204void Context::signalSemaphore(SemaphoreID semaphoreHandle,
8205 GLuint numBufferBarriers,
8206 const BufferID *buffers,
8207 GLuint numTextureBarriers,
8208 const TextureID *textures,
8209 const GLenum *dstLayouts)
8210{
8211 Semaphore *semaphore = getSemaphore(semaphoreHandle);
8212 ASSERT(semaphore);
8213
8214 BufferBarrierVector bufferBarriers(numBufferBarriers);
8215 for (GLuint bufferBarrierIdx = 0; bufferBarrierIdx < numBufferBarriers; bufferBarrierIdx++)
8216 {
8217 bufferBarriers[bufferBarrierIdx] = getBuffer(buffers[bufferBarrierIdx]);
8218 }
8219
8220 TextureBarrierVector textureBarriers(numTextureBarriers);
8221 for (GLuint textureBarrierIdx = 0; textureBarrierIdx < numTextureBarriers; textureBarrierIdx++)
8222 {
8223 textureBarriers[textureBarrierIdx].texture = getTexture(textures[textureBarrierIdx]);
8224 textureBarriers[textureBarrierIdx].layout = dstLayouts[textureBarrierIdx];
8225 }
8226
8227 ANGLE_CONTEXT_TRY(semaphore->signal(this, bufferBarriers, textureBarriers));
8228}
8229
8230void Context::importSemaphoreFd(SemaphoreID semaphore, HandleType handleType, GLint fd)

8232 Semaphore *semaphoreObject = getSemaphore(semaphore);

8269
8270bool Context::getIndexedQueryParameterInfo(GLenum target,
8271 GLenum *type,
8272 unsigned int *numParams) const
8273{
8274 if (getClientVersion() < Version(3, 0))
8275 {
8276 return false;
8277 }
8278
8279 switch (target)
8280 {
8281 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_BINDING:
8282 case GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDING:
8283 {
8284 *type = GL_INT;
8285 *numParams = 1;
8286 return true;
8287 }
8288 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_START:
8289 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_SIZE:
8290 case GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER_START:
8291 case GL_UNIFORM_BUFFER_SIZE:
8292 {
8293 *type = GL_INT_64_ANGLEX;
8294 *numParams = 1;
8295 return true;
8296 }
8297 }
8298
8299 if (mSupportedExtensions.drawBuffersIndexedAny())
8300 {
8301 switch (target)
8302 {
8303 case GL_BLEND_SRC_RGB:
8304 case GL_BLEND_SRC_ALPHA:
8305 case GL_BLEND_DST_RGB:
8306 case GL_BLEND_DST_ALPHA:
8307 case GL_BLEND_EQUATION_RGB:
8308 case GL_BLEND_EQUATION_ALPHA:
8309 {
8310 *type = GL_INT;
8311 *numParams = 1;
8312 return true;
8313 }
8314 case GL_COLOR_WRITEMASK:
8315 {
8316 *type = GL_BOOL;
8317 *numParams = 4;
8318 return true;
8319 }
8320 }
8321 }
8322
8323 if (getClientVersion() < Version(3, 1))
8324 {
8325 return false;
8326 }
8327
8328 switch (target)
8329 {
8330 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_LAYERED:
8331 {
8332 *type = GL_BOOL;
8333 *numParams = 1;
8334 return true;
8335 }
8336 case GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_COUNT:
8337 case GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE:
8338 case GL_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_BINDING:
8339 case GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDING:
8340 case GL_VERTEX_BINDING_BUFFER:
8341 case GL_VERTEX_BINDING_DIVISOR:
8342 case GL_VERTEX_BINDING_OFFSET:
8343 case GL_VERTEX_BINDING_STRIDE:
8344 case GL_SAMPLE_MASK_VALUE:
8345 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_NAME:
8346 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_LEVEL:
8347 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_LAYER:
8348 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_ACCESS:
8349 case GL_IMAGE_BINDING_FORMAT:
8350 {
8351 *type = GL_INT;
8352 *numParams = 1;
8353 return true;
8354 }
8355 case GL_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_START:
8356 case GL_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_SIZE:
8357 case GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_START:
8358 case GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_SIZE:
8359 {
8360 *type = GL_INT_64_ANGLEX;
8361 *numParams = 1;
8362 return true;
8363 }
8364 }
8365
8366 return false;
8367}
