8408
8409GLenum Context::getConvertedRenderbufferFormat(GLenum internalformat) const
8410{
8411 if (mState.mExtensions.webglCompatibility && mState.mClientVersion.major == 2 &&
8412 internalformat == GL_DEPTH_STENCIL)
8413 {
8414 return GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8;
8415 }
8416 if (getClientType() == EGL_OPENGL_API && internalformat == GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT)
8417 {
8418 return GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24;
8419 }
8420 return internalformat;
8421}
8422
8423void Context::maxShaderCompilerThreads(GLuint count)
8424{
8425 GLuint oldCount = mState.getMaxShaderCompilerThreads();
8426 mState.setMaxShaderCompilerThreads(count);
8427 // A count of zero specifies a request for no parallel compiling or linking.
8428 if ((oldCount == 0 || count == 0) && (oldCount != 0 || count != 0))
8429 {
8430 mThreadPool = angle::WorkerThreadPool::Create(count > 0);
8431 }
8432 mThreadPool->setMaxThreads(count);
8433 mImplementation->setMaxShaderCompilerThreads(count);
8434}
8435
8436bool Context::isGLES1() const
8437{
8438 return mState.getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0);
8439}
8440
8441void Context::onSubjectStateChange(angle::SubjectIndex index, angle::SubjectMessage message)
8442{
8443 switch (index)
8444 {
8445 case kVertexArraySubjectIndex:
8446 switch (message)
8447 {
8448 case angle::SubjectMessage::ContentsChanged:
8449 mState.setObjectDirty(GL_VERTEX_ARRAY);
8450 mStateCache.onVertexArrayBufferContentsChange(this);
8451 break;
8452 case angle::SubjectMessage::SubjectMapped:
8453 case angle::SubjectMessage::SubjectUnmapped:
8454 case angle::SubjectMessage::BindingChanged:
8455 mStateCache.onVertexArrayBufferStateChange(this);
8456 break;
8457 default:
8458 break;
8459 }
8460 break;
8461
8462 case kReadFramebufferSubjectIndex:
8463 switch (message)
8464 {
8465 case angle::SubjectMessage::DirtyBitsFlagged:
8466 mState.setReadFramebufferDirty();
8467 break;
8468 case angle::SubjectMessage::SurfaceChanged:
8469 mState.setReadFramebufferBindingDirty();
8470 break;
8471 default:
8472 UNREACHABLE();
8473 break;
8474 }
8475 break;
8476
8477 case kDrawFramebufferSubjectIndex:
8478 switch (message)
8479 {
8480 case angle::SubjectMessage::DirtyBitsFlagged:
8481 mState.setDrawFramebufferDirty();
8482 mStateCache.onDrawFramebufferChange(this);
8483 break;
8484 case angle::SubjectMessage::SurfaceChanged:
8485 mState.setDrawFramebufferBindingDirty();
8486 break;
8487 default:
8488 UNREACHABLE();
8489 break;
8490 }
8491 break;
8492
8493 default:
8494 if (index < kTextureMaxSubjectIndex)
8495 {
8496 if (message != angle::SubjectMessage::ContentsChanged &&
8497 message != angle::SubjectMessage::BindingChanged)
8498 {
8499 mState.onActiveTextureStateChange(this, index);
8500 mStateCache.onActiveTextureChange(this);
8501 }
8502 }
8503 else if (index < kImageMaxSubjectIndex)
8504 {
8505 mState.onImageStateChange(this, index - kImage0SubjectIndex);
8506 if (message == angle::SubjectMessage::ContentsChanged)
8507 {
8508 mState.mDirtyBits.set(State::DirtyBitType::DIRTY_BIT_IMAGE_BINDINGS);
8509 }
8510 }
8511 else if (index < kUniformBufferMaxSubjectIndex)
8512 {
8513 mState.onUniformBufferStateChange(index - kUniformBuffer0SubjectIndex);
8514 mStateCache.onUniformBufferStateChange(this);
8515 }
8516 else
8517 {
8518 ASSERT(index < kSamplerMaxSubjectIndex);
8519 mState.setSamplerDirty(index - kSampler0SubjectIndex);
8520 mState.onActiveTextureStateChange(this, index - kSampler0SubjectIndex);
8521 }
8522 break;
8523 }
8524}
8525
8526angle::Result Context::onProgramLink(Program *programObject)
8527{
8528 // Don't parallel link a program which is active in any GL contexts. With this assumption, we
8529 // don't need to worry that:
8530 // 1. Draw calls after link use the new executable code or the old one depending on the link
8531 // result.
8532 // 2. When a backend program, e.g., ProgramD3D is linking, other backend classes like
8533 // StateManager11, Renderer11, etc., may have a chance to make unexpected calls to
8534 // ProgramD3D.
8535 if (programObject->isInUse())
8536 {
8537 programObject->resolveLink(this);
8538 if (programObject->isLinked())
8539 {
8540 ANGLE_TRY(mState.onProgramExecutableChange(this, programObject));
8541 }
8542 mStateCache.onProgramExecutableChange(this);
8543 }
8544
8545 return angle::Result::Continue;
8546}
8547
8548egl::Error Context::setDefaultFramebuffer(egl::Surface *drawSurface, egl::Surface *readSurface)
8549{
8550 ASSERT(mCurrentDrawSurface == nullptr);
8551 ASSERT(mCurrentReadSurface == nullptr);
8552
8553 Framebuffer *newDefaultFramebuffer = nullptr;
8554
8555 mCurrentDrawSurface = drawSurface;
8556 mCurrentReadSurface = readSurface;
8557
8558 if (drawSurface != nullptr)
8559 {
8560 ANGLE_TRY(drawSurface->makeCurrent(this));
8561 newDefaultFramebuffer = drawSurface->createDefaultFramebuffer(this, readSurface);
8562 }
8563 else
8564 {
8565 newDefaultFramebuffer = new Framebuffer(this, mImplementation.get(), readSurface);
8566 }
8567 ASSERT(newDefaultFramebuffer);
8568
8569 if (readSurface && (drawSurface != readSurface))
8570 {
8571 ANGLE_TRY(readSurface->makeCurrent(this));
8572 }
8573
8574 // Update default framebuffer, the binding of the previous default
8575 // framebuffer (or lack of) will have a nullptr.
8576 mState.mFramebufferManager->setDefaultFramebuffer(newDefaultFramebuffer);
8577 if (mState.getDrawFramebuffer() == nullptr)
8578 {
8579 bindDrawFramebuffer(newDefaultFramebuffer->id());
8580 }
8581 if (mState.getReadFramebuffer() == nullptr)
8582 {
8583 bindReadFramebuffer(newDefaultFramebuffer->id());
8584 }
8585
8586 return egl::NoError();
8587}
8588
8589egl::Error Context::unsetDefaultFramebuffer()
8590{
8591 gl::Framebuffer *defaultFramebuffer =
8592 mState.mFramebufferManager->getFramebuffer(Framebuffer::kDefaultDrawFramebufferHandle);
8593
8594 // Remove the default framebuffer
8595 if (mState.getReadFramebuffer() == defaultFramebuffer)
8596 {
8597 mState.setReadFramebufferBinding(nullptr);
8598 mReadFramebufferObserverBinding.bind(nullptr);
8599 }
8600
8601 if (mState.getDrawFramebuffer() == defaultFramebuffer)
8602 {
8603 mState.setDrawFramebufferBinding(nullptr);
8604 mDrawFramebufferObserverBinding.bind(nullptr);
8605 }
8606
8607 if (defaultFramebuffer)
8608 {
8609 defaultFramebuffer->onDestroy(this);
8610 delete defaultFramebuffer;
8611 }
8612
8613 mState.mFramebufferManager->setDefaultFramebuffer(nullptr);
8614
8615 // Always unset the current surface, even if setIsCurrent fails.
8616 egl::Surface *drawSurface = mCurrentDrawSurface;
8617 egl::Surface *readSurface = mCurrentReadSurface;
8618 mCurrentDrawSurface = nullptr;
8619 mCurrentReadSurface = nullptr;
8620 if (drawSurface)
8621 {
8622 ANGLE_TRY(drawSurface->unMakeCurrent(this));
8623 }
8624 if (drawSurface != readSurface)
8625 {
8626 ANGLE_TRY(readSurface->unMakeCurrent(this));
8627 }
8628
8629 return egl::NoError();
8630}
8631
8632void Context::onPreSwap() const
8633{
8634 // Dump frame capture if enabled.
8635 mFrameCapture->onEndFrame(this);
8636}

8679
8680// ErrorSet implementation.
8681ErrorSet::ErrorSet(Context *context) : mContext(context) {}
8682
8683ErrorSet::~ErrorSet() = default;
8684
8685void ErrorSet::handleError(GLenum errorCode,
8686 const char *message,
8687 const char *file,
8688 const char *function,
8689 unsigned int line)
8690{
8691 if (errorCode == GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY &&
8692 mContext->getGraphicsResetStrategy() == GL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET_EXT &&
8693 mContext->getDisplay()->getFrontendFeatures().loseContextOnOutOfMemory.enabled)
8694 {
8695 mContext->markContextLost(GraphicsResetStatus::UnknownContextReset);
8696 }
8697
8698 std::stringstream errorStream;
8699 errorStream << "Error: " << gl::FmtHex(errorCode) << ", in " << file << ", " << function << ":"
8700 << line << ". " << message;
8701
8702 std::string formattedMessage = errorStream.str();
8703
8704 // Process the error, but log it with WARN severity so it shows up in logs.
8705 ASSERT(errorCode != GL_NO_ERROR);
8706 mErrors.insert(errorCode);
8707
8708 mContext->getState().getDebug().insertMessage(GL_DEBUG_SOURCE_API, GL_DEBUG_TYPE_ERROR,
8709 errorCode, GL_DEBUG_SEVERITY_HIGH, message,
8710 gl::LOG_WARN);
8711}
8712
8713void ErrorSet::validationError(GLenum errorCode, const char *message)
8714{
8715 ASSERT(errorCode != GL_NO_ERROR);
8716 mErrors.insert(errorCode);
8717
8718 mContext->getState().getDebug().insertMessage(GL_DEBUG_SOURCE_API, GL_DEBUG_TYPE_ERROR,
8719 errorCode, GL_DEBUG_SEVERITY_HIGH, message,
8720 gl::LOG_INFO);
8721}
8722
8723bool ErrorSet::empty() const
8724{
8725 return mErrors.empty();
8726}
8727
8728GLenum ErrorSet::popError()
8729{
8730 ASSERT(!empty());
8731 GLenum error = *mErrors.begin();
8732 mErrors.erase(mErrors.begin());
8733 return error;
8734}

8738 : mCachedHasAnyEnabledClientAttrib(false),
8739 mCachedNonInstancedVertexElementLimit(0),
8740 mCachedInstancedVertexElementLimit(0),
8741 mCachedBasicDrawStatesError(kInvalidPointer),
8742 mCachedBasicDrawElementsError(kInvalidPointer),
8743 mCachedTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused(false),
8744 mCachedCanDraw(false)

8749ANGLE_INLINE void StateCache::updateVertexElementLimits(Context *context)
8750{
8751 if (context->isBufferAccessValidationEnabled())
8752 {
8753 updateVertexElementLimitsImpl(context);
8754 }
8755}
8756
8757void StateCache::initialize(Context *context)
8758{
8759 updateValidDrawModes(context);
8760 updateValidBindTextureTypes(context);
8761 updateValidDrawElementsTypes(context);
8762 updateBasicDrawStatesError();
8763 updateBasicDrawElementsError();
8764 updateVertexAttribTypesValidation(context);
8765 updateCanDraw(context);
8766}
8767
8768void StateCache::updateActiveAttribsMask(Context *context)
8769{
8770 bool isGLES1 = context->isGLES1();
8771 const State &glState = context->getState();
8772
8773 if (!isGLES1 && !glState.getProgramExecutable())
8774 {
8775 mCachedActiveBufferedAttribsMask = AttributesMask();
8776 mCachedActiveClientAttribsMask = AttributesMask();
8777 mCachedActiveDefaultAttribsMask = AttributesMask();
8778 return;
8779 }
8780
8781 AttributesMask activeAttribs =
8782 isGLES1 ? glState.gles1().getActiveAttributesMask()
8783 : glState.getProgramExecutable()->getActiveAttribLocationsMask();
8784
8785 const VertexArray *vao = glState.getVertexArray();
8786 ASSERT(vao);
8787
8788 const AttributesMask &clientAttribs = vao->getClientAttribsMask();
8789 const AttributesMask &enabledAttribs = vao->getEnabledAttributesMask();
8790 const AttributesMask &activeEnabled = activeAttribs & enabledAttribs;
8791
8792 mCachedActiveClientAttribsMask = activeEnabled & clientAttribs;
8793 mCachedActiveBufferedAttribsMask = activeEnabled & ~clientAttribs;
8794 mCachedActiveDefaultAttribsMask = activeAttribs & ~enabledAttribs;
8795 mCachedHasAnyEnabledClientAttrib = (clientAttribs & enabledAttribs).any();
8796}
8797
8798void StateCache::updateVertexElementLimitsImpl(Context *context)
8799{
8800 ASSERT(context->isBufferAccessValidationEnabled());
8801
8802 const VertexArray *vao = context->getState().getVertexArray();
8803
8804 mCachedNonInstancedVertexElementLimit = std::numeric_limits<GLint64>::max();
8805 mCachedInstancedVertexElementLimit = std::numeric_limits<GLint64>::max();
8806
8807 // VAO can be null on Context startup. If we make this computation lazier we could ASSERT.
8808 // If there are no buffered attributes then we should not limit the draw call count.
8809 if (!vao || !mCachedActiveBufferedAttribsMask.any())
8810 {
8811 return;
8812 }
8813
8814 const auto &vertexAttribs = vao->getVertexAttributes();
8815 const auto &vertexBindings = vao->getVertexBindings();
8816
8817 for (size_t attributeIndex : mCachedActiveBufferedAttribsMask)
8818 {
8819 const VertexAttribute &attrib = vertexAttribs[attributeIndex];
8820
8821 const VertexBinding &binding = vertexBindings[attrib.bindingIndex];
8822 ASSERT(context->isGLES1() ||
8823 context->getState().getProgramExecutable()->isAttribLocationActive(attributeIndex));
8824
8825 GLint64 limit = attrib.getCachedElementLimit();
8826 if (binding.getDivisor() > 0)
8827 {
8828 mCachedInstancedVertexElementLimit =
8829 std::min(mCachedInstancedVertexElementLimit, limit);
8830 }
8831 else
8832 {
8833 mCachedNonInstancedVertexElementLimit =
8834 std::min(mCachedNonInstancedVertexElementLimit, limit);
8835 }
8836 }
8837}

8964
8965void StateCache::setValidDrawModes(bool pointsOK,
8966 bool linesOK,
8967 bool trisOK,
8968 bool lineAdjOK,
8969 bool triAdjOK)
8970{
8971 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::Points] = pointsOK;
8972 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::Lines] = linesOK;
8973 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::LineStrip] = linesOK;
8974 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::LineLoop] = linesOK;
8975 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::Triangles] = trisOK;
8976 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan] = trisOK;
8977 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip] = trisOK;
8978 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency] = lineAdjOK;
8979 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::LineStripAdjacency] = lineAdjOK;
8980 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency] = triAdjOK;
8981 mCachedValidDrawModes[PrimitiveMode::TriangleStripAdjacency] = triAdjOK;
8982}
8983
8984void StateCache::updateValidDrawModes(Context *context)
8985{
8986 const State &state = context->getState();
8987 Program *program = state.getProgram();
8988
8989 if (mCachedTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused)
8990 {
8991 TransformFeedback *curTransformFeedback = state.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
8992
8993 // ES Spec 3.0 validation text:
8994 // When transform feedback is active and not paused, all geometric primitives generated must
8995 // match the value of primitiveMode passed to BeginTransformFeedback. The error
8996 // INVALID_OPERATION is generated by DrawArrays and DrawArraysInstanced if mode is not
8997 // identical to primitiveMode. The error INVALID_OPERATION is also generated by
8998 // DrawElements, DrawElementsInstanced, and DrawRangeElements while transform feedback is
8999 // active and not paused, regardless of mode. Any primitive type may be used while transform
9000 // feedback is paused.
9001 if (!context->getExtensions().geometryShader)
9002 {
9003 mCachedValidDrawModes.fill(false);
9004 mCachedValidDrawModes[curTransformFeedback->getPrimitiveMode()] = true;
9005 return;
9006 }
9007
9008 // EXT_geometry_shader validation text:
9009 // When transform feedback is active and not paused, all geometric primitives generated must
9010 // be compatible with the value of <primitiveMode> passed to BeginTransformFeedback. If a
9011 // geometry shader is active, the type of primitive emitted by that shader is used instead
9012 // of the <mode> parameter passed to drawing commands for the purposes of this error check.
9013 // Any primitive type may be used while transform feedback is paused.
9014 bool pointsOK = curTransformFeedback->getPrimitiveMode() == PrimitiveMode::Points;
9015 bool linesOK = curTransformFeedback->getPrimitiveMode() == PrimitiveMode::Lines;
9016 bool trisOK = curTransformFeedback->getPrimitiveMode() == PrimitiveMode::Triangles;
9017
9018 setValidDrawModes(pointsOK, linesOK, trisOK, false, false);
9019 return;
9020 }
9021
9022 const ProgramExecutable *programExecutable = context->getState().getProgramExecutable();
9023 if (!programExecutable || !programExecutable->hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Geometry))
9024 {
9025 mCachedValidDrawModes = kValidBasicDrawModes;
9026 return;
9027 }
9028
9029 ASSERT(programExecutable->hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Geometry));
9030 PrimitiveMode gsMode = program->getGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType();
9031
9032 bool pointsOK = gsMode == PrimitiveMode::Points;
9033 bool linesOK = gsMode == PrimitiveMode::Lines;
9034 bool trisOK = gsMode == PrimitiveMode::Triangles;
9035 bool lineAdjOK = gsMode == PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency;
9036 bool triAdjOK = gsMode == PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency;
9037
9038 setValidDrawModes(pointsOK, linesOK, trisOK, lineAdjOK, triAdjOK);
9039}
9040
9041void StateCache::updateValidBindTextureTypes(Context *context)
9042{
9043 const Extensions &exts = context->getExtensions();
9044 bool isGLES3 = context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3;
9045 bool isGLES31 = context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 1);
9046
9047 mCachedValidBindTextureTypes = {{
9048 {TextureType::_2D, true},
9049 {TextureType::_2DArray, isGLES3},
9050 {TextureType::_2DMultisample, isGLES31 || exts.textureMultisample},
9051 {TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray, exts.textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES},
9052 {TextureType::_3D, isGLES3 || exts.texture3DOES},
9053 {TextureType::External, exts.eglImageExternalOES || exts.eglStreamConsumerExternalNV},
9054 {TextureType::Rectangle, exts.textureRectangle},
9055 {TextureType::CubeMap, true},
9056 {TextureType::CubeMapArray, exts.textureCubeMapArrayAny()},
9057 {TextureType::VideoImage, exts.webglVideoTexture},
9058 {TextureType::Buffer, exts.textureBufferAny()},
9059 }};
9060}
9061
9062void StateCache::updateValidDrawElementsTypes(Context *context)
9063{
9064 bool supportsUint =
9065 (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3 || context->getExtensions().elementIndexUintOES);
9066
9067 mCachedValidDrawElementsTypes = {{
9068 {DrawElementsType::UnsignedByte, true},
9069 {DrawElementsType::UnsignedShort, true},
9070 {DrawElementsType::UnsignedInt, supportsUint},
9071 }};
9072}
9073
9074void StateCache::updateTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused(Context *context)
9075{
9076 TransformFeedback *xfb = context->getState().getCurrentTransformFeedback();
9077 mCachedTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused = xfb && xfb->isActive() && !xfb->isPaused();
9078}
9079
9080void StateCache::updateVertexAttribTypesValidation(Context *context)
9081{
9082 VertexAttribTypeCase halfFloatValidity = (context->getExtensions().vertexHalfFloatOES)
9083 ? VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid
9084 : VertexAttribTypeCase::Invalid;
9085
9086 VertexAttribTypeCase vertexType1010102Validity =
9087 (context->getExtensions().vertexAttribType1010102OES) ? VertexAttribTypeCase::ValidSize3or4
9088 : VertexAttribTypeCase::Invalid;
9089
9090 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() <= 2)
9091 {
9092 mCachedVertexAttribTypesValidation = {{
9093 {VertexAttribType::Byte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9094 {VertexAttribType::Short, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9095 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedByte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9096 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedShort, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9097 {VertexAttribType::Float, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9098 {VertexAttribType::Fixed, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9099 {VertexAttribType::HalfFloatOES, halfFloatValidity},
9100 }};
9101 }
9102 else
9103 {
9104 mCachedVertexAttribTypesValidation = {{
9105 {VertexAttribType::Byte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9106 {VertexAttribType::Short, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9107 {VertexAttribType::Int, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9108 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedByte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9109 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedShort, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9110 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9111 {VertexAttribType::Float, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9112 {VertexAttribType::HalfFloat, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9113 {VertexAttribType::Fixed, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9114 {VertexAttribType::Int2101010, VertexAttribTypeCase::ValidSize4Only},
9115 {VertexAttribType::HalfFloatOES, halfFloatValidity},
9116 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt2101010, VertexAttribTypeCase::ValidSize4Only},
9117 {VertexAttribType::Int1010102, vertexType1010102Validity},
9118 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt1010102, vertexType1010102Validity},
9119 }};
9120
9121 mCachedIntegerVertexAttribTypesValidation = {{
9122 {VertexAttribType::Byte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9123 {VertexAttribType::Short, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9124 {VertexAttribType::Int, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9125 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedByte, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9126 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedShort, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9127 {VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt, VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid},
9128 }};
9129 }
9130}
9131
9132void StateCache::updateActiveShaderStorageBufferIndices(Context *context)
9133{
9134 mCachedActiveShaderStorageBufferIndices.reset();
9135 const ProgramExecutable *executable = context->getState().getProgramExecutable();
9136 if (executable)
9137 {
9138 for (const InterfaceBlock &block : executable->getShaderStorageBlocks())
9139 {
9140 mCachedActiveShaderStorageBufferIndices.set(block.binding);
9141 }
9142 }
9143}
9144
9145void StateCache::updateActiveImageUnitIndices(Context *context)
9146{
9147 mCachedActiveImageUnitIndices.reset();
9148 const ProgramExecutable *executable = context->getState().getProgramExecutable();
9149 if (executable)
9150 {
9151 for (const ImageBinding &imageBinding : executable->getImageBindings())
9152 {
9153 for (GLuint binding : imageBinding.boundImageUnits)
9154 {
9155 mCachedActiveImageUnitIndices.set(binding);
9156 }
9157 }
9158 }
9159}
9160
9161void StateCache::updateCanDraw(Context *context)
9162{
9163 mCachedCanDraw = (context->isGLES1() ||
9164 (context->getState().getProgramExecutable() &&
9165 context->getState().getProgramExecutable()->hasVertexAndFragmentShader()));
9166}
